{"title_page": "2014\u201315 FC Bayern Munich season", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} \n{{Infobox football club season\n|club               = [[FC Bayern Munich]]\n|season             = [[2014\u201315 in German football|2014\u201315]]\n|manager            = [[Pep Guardiola]]\n|chrtitle           = Sporting director\n|chairman           = [[Matthias Sammer]]\n|stadium            = [[Allianz Arena]]\n|league             = [[2014\u201315 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]]\n|league result      = '''Winners'''\n|cup1               = [[2014\u201315 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]]\n|cup1 result        = Semi-finals\n|cup2               = [[2014 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]]\n|cup2 result        = Runners-up\n|cup3               = [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]\n|cup3 result        = Semi-finals\n|league topscorer   = <br>{{Nowrap|[[Arjen Robben]] (17)<br>[[Robert Lewandowski]] (17)}}\n|season topscorer   = <br>{{Nowrap|[[Robert Lewandowski]] (25)}}\n|highest attendance = 75,000<ref group=n>Eight Bundesliga matches and two DFB-Pokal matches</ref>\n|lowest attendance  = 68,000<ref group=n>Three UEFA Champions League group stage matches</ref>\n|average attendance = 72,882<ref>{{cite web|title=Statistics|url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/bayern-munich/132/statistics/performance?leagueId=10&season=2014|website=[[ESPN FC]]|accessdate=4 August 2015}}</ref>\n|largest win        = <span style=\"font-size:smaller\">{{Nowrap|FC Bayern Munich 8\u20130 Hamburger SV}}</span>\n|largest loss       = <span style=\"font-size:smaller\">{{Nowrap|VfL Wolfsburg 4\u20131 FC Bayern Munich<br>FC Barcelona 3\u20130 FC Bayern Munich}}</span>\n|pattern_la1        = _bayern1415home\n|pattern_b1         = _FCBAYERN_1415h\n|pattern_ra1        = _bayern1415home\n|pattern_sh1        = _adidaswhite\n|pattern_so1        = _FCBAYERN_1415h\n|leftarm1           = DD0000\n|body1              = FFFFFF\n|rightarm1          = DD0000\n|shorts1            = DD0000\n|socks1             = FFFFFF\n|pattern_la2        = _bayern1415a\n|pattern_b2         = _bayern1415A\n|pattern_ra2        = _bayern1415a\n|pattern_sh2        = _bayern1415a\n|pattern_so2        = _bayern1415a\n|leftarm2           = FFFFFF\n|body2              = FFFFFF\n|rightarm2          = FFFFFF\n|shorts2            = FFFFFF\n|socks2             = FFFFFF\n|pattern_la3        = _fcb1415t\n|pattern_b3         = _bayern1415T\n|pattern_ra3        = _fcb1415t\n|pattern_sh3        = _fcb1415t\n|pattern_so3        = _fcb1415t\n|leftarm3           = 000000\n|body3              = 000000\n|rightarm3          = 000000\n|shorts3            = 000000\n|socks3             = 000000\n|updated            = 12 May 2015\n|prevseason         = [[2013\u201314 FC Bayern Munich season|2013\u201314]]\n|nextseason         = [[2015\u201316 FC Bayern Munich season|2015\u201316]]\n}}\n\nThe '''[[2014\u201315 in German football|2014\u201315]] [[FC Bayern Munich]] [[List of FC Bayern Munich seasons|season]]''' was the 116th season in the club's history and the 50th consecutive season in the top flight of German [[Association football|football]], the [[Bundesliga]], since their promotion from the [[Regionalliga S\u00fcd (1963\u201374)|Regionalliga S\u00fcd]] in 1965. Bayern participated in the season's editions of the [[2014\u201315 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]], [[2014 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]] and [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]. It was the 10th season for Bayern in the [[Allianz Arena]].\n\n==Background==\n\n===Overview===\n\n====Context====\nBayern came into the 2014\u201315 season as the defending [[2013\u201314 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] champions<ref name=\"Der FC Bayern feiert die erste M\u00e4rz-Meisterschaft\">{{cite news|title=Der FC Bayern feiert die erste M\u00e4rz-Meisterschaft|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/hertha-bsc/article126177497/Der-FC-Bayern-feiert-die-erste-Maerz-Meisterschaft.html|accessdate=22 August 2014|publisher=[[Die Welt]]|date=25 March 2014|language=German}}</ref> and defending [[2013\u201314 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] champions.<ref name=\"Arjen Robben bezwingt erneut den BVB\">{{cite news|last=Meininghaus|first=Felix|title=Arjen Robben bezwingt erneut den BVB|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-im-dfb-pokalfinale-robbens-tor-bezwingt-erneut-den-bvb-1.1968101|accessdate=22 August 2014|newspaper=[[S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung]]|date=17 May 2014|location=Berlin|language=German}}</ref> In the [[2013\u201314 FC Bayern Munich season|2013\u201314 season]], Bayern were knocked-out of Champions League by eventual winners [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] in the semifinals, losing 5\u20130 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ramos setzt Bayerns Finaltraum fr\u00fch ein Ende|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2013-14/9/2393112/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_real-madrid.html|accessdate=22 August 2014|newspaper=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]]|date=29 April 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern hired Michael Reschke as Technical Director.<ref name=\"Sammer freut sich auf Reschke - Can-Deal fix\">{{cite news|last=Lu\u00dfem|first=Frank|title=Sammer freut sich auf Reschke - Can-Deal fix|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/605657/artikel_sammer-freut-sich-auf-reschke---can-deal-fix.html|accessdate=5 June 2014|publisher=kicker|date=5 June 2014|language=German}}</ref> This is a new position and will provide \"support\" for [[Matthias Sammer]], the Sporting Director for Bayern.<ref name=\"Sammer freut sich auf Reschke - Can-Deal fix\"/>\n\n====Transfers====\n[[File:Xabi Alonso FCB.jpg|thumb|152px|Xabi Alonso joined Bayern in August 2014]]\n\n[[Robert Lewandowski]],<ref name=\"Robert Lewandowski unterschreibt bis 2019\"/> [[Sebastian Rode]],<ref name=\"FC Bayern best\u00e4tigt Verpflichtung von Rode\"/> [[Juan Bernat]],<ref name=\"FC Bayern verpflichtet Linksverteidiger Bernat\"/> [[Pepe Reina]],<ref name=\"Liverpool: Pepe Reina joins Bayern Munich in a three-year deal\"/> [[Medhi Benatia]],<ref name=\"Medhi Benatia: Bayern Munich sign Roma defender\"/> [[Xabi Alonso]],<ref name=\"Xabi Alonso gegen Schalke schon im Bayern-Kader\"/> and [[Sinan Kurt]]<ref name=\"Einigung erzielt: Gladbachs Kurt wechselt zum FC Bayern\"/> transferred to Bayern. Lewandowski was the second \"key\" player within a year to move to Bayern from [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref name=\"Robert Lewandowski to join Bayern Munich from Borussia Dortmund\"/> Bayern bought [[Medhi Benatia]] from [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref name=\"Medhi Benatia: Bayern Munich sign Roma defender\"/> [[Pep Guardiola]] wanted to sign another player due to [[Javi Mart\u00ednez]]'s injury in the [[2014 DFL-Supercup|German Super Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Pep Guardiola: Bayern Munich need to sign another player|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28819887|accessdate=16 August 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=16 August 2014}}</ref> For this reason, Bayern brought [[Xabi Alonso]] from Real Madrid<ref name=\"Xabi Alonso gegen Schalke schon im Bayern-Kader\"/> for undisclosed fee. [[Lukas Raeder]],<ref name=\"Transfer news: Lukas Raeder confirms Bayern Munich exit\"/> [[Alessandro Sch\u00f6pf]],<ref name=\"Club holt Bayern-Talent Sch\u00f6pf\"/> [[Mario Mand\u017euki\u0107]],<ref name=\"Mario Mandzukic joins Atletico Madrid from Bayern Munich\"/> [[Toni Kroos]],<ref name=\"Toni Kroos joins Real Madrid from Bayern Munich\"/> and [[Diego Contento]]<ref name=\"Contento venu pour Sagnol\"/> left the club. Contento had been at the club for 19 years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Contento wechselt nach Bordeaux|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fussball-bundesliga-contento-wechselt-nach-bordeaux-1.2083645|accessdate=12 August 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=9 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Mand\u017euki\u0107 wanted to leave Bayern because the \"playing style of coach Pep Guardiola simply does not fit him.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Es ist das Beste, dass wir uns trennen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/mario-mandzukic-beim-fc-bayern-das-beste-dass-wir-uns-trennen-1.1991717|accessdate=9 June 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=9 June 2014|language=German}}</ref> [[Julian Green]] was loaned out to [[Hamburger SV]]<ref name=\"Bayern loan Julian Green to Hamburg, sign Monchengladbach's Sinan Kurt\"/> and [[Daniel Van Buyten]] retired.<ref name='Van Buyten: \"Mein K\u00f6rper hat genug gelitten\"'/> He had been offered another role at Bayern.<ref>{{cite news|title=Daniel van Buyten quitte le Bayern Munich|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Van-buyten-s-en-va/468738|accessdate=31 May 2014|newspaper=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]|date=27 May 2014|language=French}}</ref>\n\n====Pre-season====\nPre-season started on 9 July.<ref>{{cite news|title=Muskelfaserriss: Saison-Aus f\u00fcr Alaba|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/Muskelfaserriss-Saison-Aus-fuer-Alaba/144058076|accessdate=20 May 2014|newspaper=[[\u00d6sterreich (newspaper)|\u00d6sterreich]]|date=20 May 2014|language=German}}</ref> During pre-season, Bayern defeated Red Baroons Dietmannsried 3\u20130 on 18 July in its first friendly match of the season.<ref name=\"Bayern siegt bei Badstuber-Comeback\">{{cite news|title=Bayern siegt bei Badstuber-Comeback|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/608262/artikel_bayern-siegt-bei-badstuber-comeback.html|accessdate=18 July 2014|publisher=kicker|date=18 July 2014|language=German}}</ref> This was [[Holger Badstuber]]'s first match in 594 days.<ref name=\"Bayern siegt bei Badstuber-Comeback\"/> Badstuber injured his ACL against [[Borussia Dortmund]] on 1 December 2012.<ref name=\"Kroos und G\u00f6tze machen das Remis klar\">{{cite news|title=Kroos und G\u00f6tze machen das Remis klar|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/spieltag/1-bundesliga/2012-13/15/1441769/spielanalyse_bayern-muenchen-14_borussia-dortmund-17.html|accessdate=18 July 2014|newspaper=kicker|date=1 December 2012|language=German}}</ref> and re-injured it on 19 May 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Das k\u00f6nnte Badstuber sogar die WM kosten|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article116334764/Das-koennte-Badstuber-sogar-die-WM-kosten.html|accessdate=18 July 2014|newspaper=Die Welt|date=19 May 2013|author=R\u00f6\u00dfner, J\u00f6rg|author2=Wolff, Julien|language=German}}</ref> He returned to first-team training on 5 May 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Badstuber absolviert erstes Mannschaftstraining|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article127658966/Badstuber-absolviert-erstes-Mannschaftstraining.html|accessdate=6 May 2014|newspaper=Die Welt|date=5 May 2014|language=German}}</ref> Also in pre-season, Bayern faced [[MSV Duisburg]] on 21 July in a benefits match<ref>{{cite news|title=FC Bayern kommt zum Benefizspiel|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/startseite/604212/artikel_fc-bayern-kommt-zum-benefizspiel.html|accessdate=12 May 2014|newspaper=kicker|date=10 May 2014|language=German}}</ref> which ended in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref name=\"Ein Treffer zum Einstand\">{{cite news|title=Ein Treffer zum Einstand|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/lewandowski-debuet-beim-fc-bayern-ein-treffer-zum-einstand-1.2056832|accessdate=21 July 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=21 July 2014|language=German}}</ref> Robert Lewandowski made his pre-season debut and scored his first goal for Bayern.<ref name=\"Ein Treffer zum Einstand\"/> Pre-season continued with the [[Telekom Cup#Telekom Cup 2014|2014 Telekom Cup]].<ref name=\"Kruse trifft dreimal vom Punkt, Bayern jubelt\">{{cite news|title=Kruse trifft dreimal vom Punkt, Bayern jubelt|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/liga-total-cup-fb-1/2014/1/2574929/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_borussia-mgladbach-15.html|accessdate=26 July 2014|work=kicker|date=26 July 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern faced [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] in the semifinal on 26 July which Bayern won in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]], after a 2\u20132 draw in sixty minutes.<ref name=\"Kruse trifft dreimal vom Punkt, Bayern jubelt\"/> Bayern defeated [[VfL Wolfsburg]] 3\u20130 in the final the following day and won the [[Telekom Cup#Telekom Cup 2014|cup]].<ref name=\"Bayern zaubert sich zum ersten Titel\">{{cite news|title=Bayern zaubert sich zum ersten Titel|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/liga-total-cup-fb-1/2014/3/2575956/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_vfl-wolfsburg-24.html|accessdate=27 July 2014|work=kicker|date=27 July 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern took a tour of the United States.<ref name=\"Werbefiguren f\u00fcr einen Tag\">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Werbefiguren f\u00fcr einen Tag|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fc-bayern-auf-us-tour-werbefiguren-fuer-einen-tag-1.2068588|accessdate=30 July 2014|work=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=30 July 2014|language=German}}</ref> This is Bayern's first pre-season tour in the United States in a decade.<ref name=\"MLS All-Stars shock Bayern Munich\">{{cite news|title=MLS All-Stars shock Bayern Munich|url=http://www.espnfc.us/major-league-soccer/match/402987/mls-all-stars-bayern-munich/report|accessdate=7 August 2014|agency=[[Associated Press]]|website=ESPN FC|date=7 August 2014}}</ref> Bayern were in New York City for three days.<ref name=\"Bayern planen Eroberung Amerikas in sieben Tagen\">{{cite news|title=Bayern planen Eroberung Amerikas in sieben Tagen|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article130685061/Bayern-planen-Eroberung-Amerikas-in-sieben-Tagen.html|accessdate=30 July 2014|work=Die Welt|date=30 July 2014|language=German}}</ref> During the tour, on 31 July,<ref name=\"GUADALAJARA VS. BAYERN M\u00dcNCHEN 0 - 1\">{{cite web|title=GUADALAJARA VS. BAYERN M\u00dcNCHEN 0 - 1|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/08/01/world/club-friendlies/club-guadalajara/fc-bayern-munchen/1688209/|accessdate=8 December 2014|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> they defeated [[C.D. Guadalajara|Chivas Guadalajara]] 1\u20130 at [[Red Bull Arena (New Jersey)|Red Bull Arena]] in [[Harrison, New Jersey]] and won the Audi Football Summit Cup 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Claudio Pizarro supplies victory|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-bundesliga/story/1968365/bayern-1-0-chivas-claudio-pizarro-supplies-victory|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=31 July 2014|date=31 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Audi Football Summit to Take Place in New Jersey This July|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/05/15/idUSnMKWfFwgHa+1d2+MKW20140515|accessdate=4 August 2014|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=15 May 2014}}</ref> Bayern were also in [[Portland, Oregon]] for four days.<ref name=\"Bayern planen Eroberung Amerikas in sieben Tagen\"/> While in Portland, on 6 August,<ref name=\"MLS ALL STAR TEAM VS. BAYERN M\u00dcNCHEN 2 - 1\">{{cite web|title=MLS ALL STAR TEAM VS. BAYERN M\u00dcNCHEN 2 - 1|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/08/07/world/hybrid-friendlies/mls-all-star-team/fc-bayern-munchen/1872733/|accessdate=8 December 2014|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> Bayern lost to the [[2014 MLS All-Star Game|MLS All-Star team]] 2\u20131 on 6 August.<ref>{{cite news|title=USA-Reise endet mit \u00c4rger|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fc-bayern/USA-Reise-endet-mit-Aerger-id30937017.html|accessdate=7 August 2014|work=[[Augsburger Allgemeine]]|date=7 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Pep Guardiola was angry because of \"harsh challenges\" and didn't shake [[Caleb Porter]]'s hand after the game.<ref name=\"MLS All-Stars shock Bayern Munich\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=MLS All-Stars beat Bayern Munich in feisty friendly|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28685673|accessdate=8 August 2014|work=BBC Sports|date=7 August 2014}}</ref> Two of the tackles came from [[Osvaldo Alonso]] and other tackle came from [[Will Johnson (soccer)|Will Johnson]].<ref name=\"Schweinsteiger verletzt - Guardiola stinksauer\">{{cite news|title=Schweinsteiger verletzt - Guardiola stinksauer|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/609291/artikel_schweinsteiger-verletzt---guardiola-stinksauer.html|accessdate=7 August 2014|work=kicker|date=7 August 2014}}</ref> The tackle by Johnson injured [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]].<ref name=\"Schweinsteiger verletzt - Guardiola stinksauer\"/> During pre-season, [[Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara|Thiago]] \"suffered a relapse\" of his knee injury that he picked up in March 2014.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich\u2019s Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara suffers setback with knee injury\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich's Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara suffers setback with knee injury|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/aug/11/thiago-alcantara-bayern-munich-injury-setback|accessdate=12 August 2014|work=The Guardian|date=11 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Mid-season====\nPrior to the winter break, Bayern signed [[Tom Starke]] to a contract extension and gave [[Gianluca Gaudino]] his first professional contract.<ref name=\"Gianluca Gaudino nun Profi - Starke verl\u00e4ngert\"/> Bayern defeated [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] and immediately went on winter break.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich players put through their paces during first training session of 2015 ahead of Bundesliga return\">{{cite news|last1=Godden|first1=Nicholas|title=Bayern Munich players put through their paces during first training session of 2015 ahead of Bundesliga return|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2900970/Bayern-Munich-players-paces-training-session-2015-ahead-Bundesliga-return.html|accessdate=7 January 2015|publisher=[[Daily Mail]]|date=7 January 2015}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=November 2019}} During the winter break, Bayern signed [[Joshua Kimmich]] as their first transfer signing for the [[2015\u201316 FC Bayern Munich season|2015\u201316 season]].<ref name=\"FC Bayern verpflichtet Joshua Kimmich\"/> Most of the players returned on 7 January.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich players put through their paces during first training session of 2015 ahead of Bundesliga return\"/> [[David Alaba]], [[Holger Badstuber]], [[Pierre-Emile H\u00f8jbjerg]], [[Medhi Benatia]], and [[Tom Starke]] had returned earlier.<ref name=\"David Alaba returns to individual training for Bayern Munich\">{{cite news|last1=Uersfeld|first1=Stephan|title=David Alaba returns to individual training for Bayern Munich|url=http://www.espnfc.com/bayern-munich/story/2230325/david-alaba-returns-individual-training-bayern-munich|accessdate=7 January 2015|date=6 January 2015}}</ref> Bayern loaned out H\u00f8jbjerg for the remainder of the season<ref name=\"H\u00f6jbjerg: Ausleihe zu Augsburg perfekt\"/> and sold [[Xherdan Shaqiri]].<ref name=\"Shaqiri: Fix bei Inter Mailand\"/> H\u00f8jbjerg also received a contract extension.<ref name=\"Hojbjerg-Leihe best\u00e4tigt - Vertrag verl\u00e4ngert!\"/> Bayern left for a nine-day training camp in [[Doha]], Qatar on 9 January.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich stars fill their boots as Pep Guardiola prepares for nine-day Doha training camp\">{{cite news|last1=Augustus|first1=Luke|title=Bayern Munich stars fill their boots as Pep Guardiola prepares for nine-day Doha training camp|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2903137/Bayern-Munich-stars-boots-Pep-Guardiola-s-prepare-nine-day-Doha-training-camp-trip.html|accessdate=10 January 2015|publisher=Daily Mail|date=9 January 2015}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=November 2019}} [[Philipp Lahm]] and Thiago didn't go to Doha, Qatar.<ref name=\"Bayern dominate UEFA Team of the Year poll\">{{cite news|title=Bayern dominate UEFA Team of the Year poll|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-dominate-uefa-team-of-the-year-poll/a-18182680|accessdate=11 January 2015|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=9 January 2015}}</ref> While in the Middle East, Bayern played two friendlies.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich stars fill their boots as Pep Guardiola prepares for nine-day Doha training camp\"/> In the first match in Qatar, Bayern defeated the Qatar Stars League XI 4\u20131.<ref name=\"Mitchell Weiser dreht bei Testspielsieg auf\">{{cite news|title=Mitchell Weiser dreht bei Testspielsieg auf|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fc-bayern/Mitchell-Weiser-dreht-bei-Testspielsieg-auf-id32635587.html|accessdate=17 January 2015|publisher=Augsburger Allgemeine|date=14 January 2015|language=German}}</ref> In the second match in [[Riyadh]], Saudi Arabia, Bayern defeated [[Al-Hilal FC|Al-Hilal]] 4\u20131.<ref name=\"Bayern mit 4:1-Sieg bei Alaba-Comeback in Saudi-Arabien\">{{cite news|title=Bayern mit 4:1-Sieg bei Alaba-Comeback in Saudi-Arabien|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/top-news/Bayern-mit-4-1-Sieg-bei-Alaba-Comeback-in-Saudi-Arabien-id32677777.html|accessdate=17 January 2015|publisher=Augsburger Allgemeine|date=17 January 2015|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished mid-season training with a 5\u20131 win against [[VfL Bochum]] on 23 January.<ref name=\"Bochum 1-5 Bayern Munich: Arjen Robben nets twice on his 31st birthday as Pep Guardiola's side win club friendly\"/> On 13 January, [[Allianz Arena]] increased capacity to 75,000 after the city of [[Munich]] approved the increase<ref name=\"Bayern in der R\u00fcckrunde vor 75.000 Zuschauern\">{{cite news|title=Bayern in der R\u00fcckrunde vor 75.000 Zuschauern|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/618973/artikel_bayern-in-der-rueckrunde-vor-75-000-zuschauern.html|accessdate=17 January 2015|publisher=kicker|date=13 January 2015|language=German}}</ref> which is for [[Bundesliga]] matches only.<ref name=\"Bayern in der R\u00fcckrunde vor 75.000 Zuschauern\"/> The capacity for [[UEFA Champions League]] matches also increased.<ref name=\"Bayern in der R\u00fcckrunde vor 75.000 Zuschauern\"/>\n\n===Transfers and contracts===\n\n====In====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" Style=\"text-align: left\"\n|-\n! {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! {{Abbr|Pos.