r>18:00\n| [[King Fahd International Stadium|A]]\n| [[Al-Hilal FC|Al-Hilal]]\n| 4\u20131\n| \u2014\n| [[Dante (footballer)|Dante]] {{goal|9}}<br>[[Bastian Schweinsteiger|Schweinsteiger]] {{goal|11}}<br>[[Robert Lewandowski|Lewandowski]] {{goal|39}}<br>[[Claudio Pizarro|Pizarro]] {{goal|62}}<br>[[Mitchell Weiser|Weiser]] {{yel|90+2}}\n| [[Rodrigo J\u00fanior Paula Silva|Dig\u00e3o]] {{yel|57}}<br>[[Abdullaziz Al-Dawsari|Al-Dawsari]] {{goal|90}}\n|<ref name=\"Bayern mit 4:1-Sieg bei Alaba-Comeback in Saudi-Arabien\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n| 23 January<br>18:00\n| [[Ruhrstadion|A]]\n| [[VfL Bochum]]\n| 5\u20131\n| 29,299\n| [[Arjen Robben|Robben]] {{goal|26||78}}<br>[[Dante (footballer)|Dante]] {{goal|43}}<br>[[Mario G\u00f6tze|G\u00f6tze]] {{goal|66}}<br>[[Sebastian Rode|Rode]] {{goal|84}}\n| [[Danny Latza|Latza]] {{goal|5}}\n| <ref name=\"Bochum 1-5 Bayern Munich: Arjen Robben nets twice on his 31st birthday as Pep Guardiola's side win club friendly\">{{cite news|last1=Nagle|first1=Ben|title=Bochum 1-5 Bayern Munich: Arjen Robben nets twice on his 31st birthday as Pep Guardiola's side win club friendly|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2923958/Bochum-1-5-Bayern-Munich-Arjen-Robben-nets-twice-31st-birthday-Pep-Guardiola-s-win-club-friendly.html|accessdate=24 January 2015|publisher=Daily Mail|date=23 January 2015}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=November 2019}}\n|}\n\n==Bundesliga==\n{{main|2014\u201315 Bundesliga}}\n\n===Bundesliga review===\n\n====August====\nBayern defeated [[VfL Wolfsburg]] 2\u20131 on 22 August<ref name=md1/> in the opening match of the Bundesliga season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dunbar|first1=Ross|title=Bayern to open season against Wolfsburg as Bundesliga fixtures confirmed|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-to-open-season-against-wolfsburg-as-bundesliga-fixtures-confirmed/a-17733107|accessdate=25 June 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=24 June 2014}}</ref> [[Thomas M\u00fcller]] and [[Arjen Robben]] scored for Bayern and [[Ivica Oli\u0107]] scored for Wolfsburg.<ref name=md1/><ref name=\"M\u00fchsam zur\u00fcck ins Alltagsgesch\u00e4ft\">{{cite news|title=M\u00fchsam zur\u00fcck ins Alltagsgesch\u00e4ft|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bundesliga-auftakt-des-fc-bayern-muehsam-zurueck-ins-alltagsgeschaeft-1.2100470|accessdate=23 August 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=22 August 2014|pages=1\u20132|language=German}}</ref> [[Junior Malanda]] failed to convert an opportunity that would have equalised for Wolfsburg.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich 2 1 VfL Wolfsburg\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich 2 1 VfL Wolfsburg|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28874605|accessdate=23 August 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=22 August 2014}}</ref> The original shot came off [[Manuel Neuer]] then off the crossbar.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich 2 1 VfL Wolfsburg\"/> Then after the ball hit the crossbar, Malanda missed from a yard out.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich 2 1 VfL Wolfsburg\"/> Bayern had chances to score more goals. [[Sebastian Rode]] had a goal wrongly ruled out<ref name=\"M\u00fchsam zur\u00fcck ins Alltagsgesch\u00e4ft\"/><ref name=\"Bayern open new Bundesliga season with win\">{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Jonathan|title=Bayern open new Bundesliga season with win|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-open-new-bundesliga-season-with-win/a-17872877|accessdate=23 August 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=22 August 2014}}</ref> after the assistant referee flagged for offside<ref name=\"M\u00fchsam zur\u00fcck ins Alltagsgesch\u00e4ft\"/> and Arjen Robben hit the crossbar.<ref name=\"Bayern open new Bundesliga season with win\"/> [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]], [[Rafinha (footballer, born 1985)|Rafinha]], [[Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara|Thiago]], [[Franck Rib\u00e9ry]], and [[Javi Mart\u00ednez]] were out injured.<ref name=md1/> [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng]] finished his two-match suspension which he received during the 2013\u201314 season.<ref name=\"Boateng verpasst Saisonauftakt\"/> [[Robert Lewandowski]], [[Juan Bernat]] made their league debuts for Bayern.<ref name=md1/> [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng]] finished his two-match suspension which he received during the 2013\u201314 season.<ref name=\"Boateng verpasst Saisonauftakt\"/> 17 year-old [[Gianluca Gaudino]] made his first Bundesliga appearance of his career and 18-year-old [[Lucas Scholl]] was on the bench for the first team for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gaudino begeistert sogar Bundestrainer L\u00f6w|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article131513579/Gaudino-begeistert-sogar-Bundestrainer-Loew.html|accessdate=22 August 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=22 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday tied for third with [[Hannover 96]].<ref name=\"md1t\"/> Then, on matchday two on 30 August, Bayern finished August with a 1\u20131 draw against [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on 30 August.<ref name=md2/> [[Robert Lewandowski]] scored for Bayern and [[Benedikt H\u00f6wedes]] scored for Schalke 04.<ref name=md2/> Lewandowski's goal was his first competitive goal for Bayern.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich denied win as Schalke claim 1-1 draw in Alonso debut\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich denied win as Schalke claim 1-1 draw in Alonso debut|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-bundesliga/story/2012895/bayern-munich-denied-win-as-schalke-claim-1-1-draw-in-alonso-debut|accessdate=30 August 2014|agency=PA Sports|publisher=ESPN FC|date=30 August 2014}}</ref> Bayern disputed H\u00f6wedes' goal after it came off his arm.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich denied win as Schalke claim 1-1 draw in Alonso debut\"/><ref name=\"Umstrittenes Hand-Tor bringt Schalke einen Punkt\">{{cite news|title=Umstrittenes Hand-Tor bringt Schalke einen Punkt|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-schalke-04/article131749632/Umstrittenes-Hand-Tor-bringt-Schalke-einen-Punkt.html|accessdate=30 August 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=30 August 2014|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=FC Schalke 04 1 1 Bayern Munich|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28985924|accessdate=1 September 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=30 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern managed 10 shots on target, which was the worst total for Bayern since [[Pep Guardiola]] took over as head coach.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chase|first1=Jefferson|title=3 key points about Bayern and the Bundesliga|url=http://www.dw.de/3-key-points-about-bayern-and-the-bundesliga/a-17891733|accessdate=1 September 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=31 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> This was Schalke 04's first point against Bayern since 10 December 2010.<ref name=\"Umstrittenes Hand-Tor bringt Schalke einen Punkt\"/> [[Xabi Alonso]] made his debut.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aleythe|first1=Saskia|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayerns-remis-gegen-schalke-ausgelaugt-vom-huetchenspiel-1.2110087|title=Ausgelaugt vom H\u00fctchenspiel|accessdate=30 August 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=30 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday tied for fifth with [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref name=md2t/>\n\n====September====\nBayern started September with a 2\u20130 win against [[VfB Stuttgart]] on matchday three on 13 September.<ref name=md3/> [[Mario G\u00f6tze]] and [[Franck Rib\u00e9ry]] scored for Bayern.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern nehmen dank Rib\u00e9ry und G\u00f6tze Fahrt auf|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article132217829/Bayern-nehmen-dank-Ribery-und-Goetze-Fahrt-auf.html|accessdate=13 September 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=13 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> [[Holger Badstuber]] left the match with a thigh injury.<ref>{{cite news|title=Badstubers Blessur wirft Systemfrage auf|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/611746/artikel_badstubers-blessur-wirft-systemfrage-auf.html|accessdate=13 September 2014|publisher=kicker|date=13 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in second place.<ref name=md3t/> Then, on matchday four on 20 September, the match against [[Hamburger SV]] finished in a 0\u20130 draw.<ref name=md4/> Guardiola decided to rotate players<ref name=\"Wir waren brennend hei\u00df heute\">{{cite news|last1=Sonnabend|first1=Lisa|title=Wir waren brennend hei\u00df heute|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/hsv-remis-gegen-fc-bayern-wir-waren-brennend-heiss-heute-1.2138756|accessdate=20 September 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=20 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> from their midweek Champions League match. Thomas M\u00fcller was on the substitutes bench, however, he replaced Arjen Robben in starting line-up after Robben was injured during the warm-up.<ref name=\"Wir waren brennend hei\u00df heute\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in fourth place.<ref name=md4t/> On matchday five, on 23 September, Bayern defeated [[SC Paderborn 07|Paderborn 07]] 4\u20130<ref name=md5/> with two goals from Mario G\u00f6tze and a goal each from Robert Lewandowski and Thomas M\u00fcller.<ref>{{cite news|title=G\u00f6tze f\u00fchrt den FC Bayern an die Tabellenspitze|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article132547960/Goetze-fuehrt-den-FC-Bayern-an-die-Tabellenspitze.html|accessdate=23 September 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=23 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md5t/> On matchday six, on 27 September, Bayern defeated [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]] 2\u20130<ref name=md6/> with a goal from Mario G\u00f6tze and an own goal from [[Daniel Halfar]].<ref>{{cite news|title=2:0 - FC Bayern eine Nummer zu gro\u00df f\u00fcr K\u00f6ln|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/news/sport/fussball-20---fc-bayern-eine-nummer-zu-gross-fuer-koeln-dpa.urn-newsml-dpa-com-20090101-140927-99-03200|accessdate=27 September 2014|agency=[[Deutsche Presse-Agentur]]|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=27 September 2014|location=Cologne|language=German}}</ref> Bayern were denied a penalty shot, again, after Arjen Robben went down.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u00dcberlegene Bayern setzen sich schon wieder oben ab|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/1-fc-koeln/article132685676/Ueberlegene-Bayern-setzen-sich-schon-wieder-oben-ab.html|accessdate=27 September 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=27 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> Xabi Alonso broke the record for having the most touches on the ball in a single match.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ph\u00e4nomen Alonso \u2013 Alle 26 Sekunden ein Ballkontakt|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article132700262/Phaenomen-Alonso-Alle-26-Sekunden-ein-Ballkontakt.html|accessdate=28 September 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=28 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=\"md6t\"/>\n\n====October====\nBayern started October with a 4\u20130 win against [[Hannover 96]] on matchday seven on 4 October.<ref name=md7/> Both Robert Lewandowski and Arjen Robben scored two goals each.<ref>{{cite news|title=4:0! Bayern schie\u00dfen Hannover ab|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/40-Bayern-schiessen-Hannover-ab/160032394|accessdate=4 October 2014|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=4 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> Xabi Alonso took a shot from just inside his own half, which was subsequently tipped over the crossbar.<ref>{{cite news|title=Robert Lewandowski and Arjen Robben score braces in Bayern rout|url=http://www.espnfc.com/german-bundesliga/story/2070852/robert-lewandowski-and-arjen-robben-score-braces-in-bayern-rout|accessdate=4 October 2014|agency=PA Sports|publisher=ESPN FC|date=4 October 2014}}</ref> With the win, Bayern got their 23rd win in 26 matches in [[Munich]] against Hannover.<ref name=md7/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md7t/> Bayern then defeated [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] 6\u20130<ref name=\"Werders Manager Eichin geht auf die Spieler los\">{{cite news|title=Werders Manager Eichin geht auf die Spieler los|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article133417496/Werders-Manager-Eichin-geht-auf-die-Spieler-los.html|accessdate=18 October 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=18 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> on matchday eight on 18 October with two goals from [[Philipp Lahm]], two goals from Mario G\u00f6tze, and a goal each from Xabi Alonso and Thomas M\u00fcller.<ref name=md8/> Alonso's goal was his first goal since transferring to Bayern.<ref name=\"Werders Manager Eichin geht auf die Spieler los\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md8t/> Then on 26 October, on matchday nine,<ref name=md9t/> [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] ended Bayern's six-match winning streak in all competitions<ref name=\"Monchengladbach halt Bayern Munich's winning run in stalemate\">{{cite news|title=Monchengladbach halt Bayern Munich's winning run in stalemate|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-bundesliga/story/2111205/monchengladbach-halt-bayern-munichs-winning-run-in-stalemate|accessdate=26 October 2014|agency=PA Sports|publisher=ESPN FC|date=26 October 2014}}</ref> with a 0\u20130 draw.<ref name=md9/> Bayern had a chance to win four consecutive league matches for the first time in 47 years.<ref name=\"Schlager ohne Robben\">{{cite news|title=Schlager ohne Robben|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fc-bayern-gegen-gladbach-schlager-ohne-robben-1.2190312|accessdate=27 October 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=26 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach's tactics against Bayern was to crowd the penalty area and play counterattacking football.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chase|first1=Jefferson|title=Gladbach stymie Bayern, Wolfsburg thrash Mainz|url=http://www.dw.de/gladbach-stymie-bayern-wolfsburg-thrash-mainz/a-18022284|accessdate=27 October 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=26 October 2014}}</ref> [[Yann Sommer]] made a fingertip save from a [[David Alaba]] shot that hit the post.<ref name=\"Monchengladbach halt Bayern Munich's winning run in stalemate\"/> Arjen Robben was injured for the match.<ref name=\"Schlager ohne Robben\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md9t/>\n\n====November====\nBayern started November with a 2\u20131 win against [[Borussia Dortmund]],<ref name=\"BVB Richtung Abstiegskampf gedr\u00e4ngt\">{{cite news|last1=Catuogno|first1=Claudio|title=BVB Richtung Abstiegskampf gedr\u00e4ngt|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/-sieg-des-fc-bayern-bvb-richtung-abstiegskampf-gedraengt-1.2196311|accessdate=1 November 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=1 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> on matchday 10, 1 November.<ref name=md10/> Robert Lewandowski and Arjen Robben scored for Bayern and [[Marco Reus]] for Borussia Dortmund.<ref name=md10/> A Marco Reus header<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 2 1 Bor Dortmd\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Mun 2 1 Bor Dortmd|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29848613|accessdate=2 November 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=1 November 2014}}</ref> gave Dortmund the lead<ref name=\"Bayern restore four-point lead to send Dortmund into bottom three\">{{cite news|title=Bayern restore four-point lead to send Dortmund into bottom three|url=http://www.espnfc.com/german-bundesliga/match/396910/bayern-munich-borussia-dortmund/report|accessdate=1 November 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=1 November 2014}}</ref> in the 31st minute.<ref name=md10/> In the second half,<ref name=md10/> [[Neven Suboti\u0107]] stopped a through-ball from Franck Rib\u00e9ry to Robben.<ref name=\"A tale of two substitutes\">{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Jonathan|title=A tale of two substitutes|url=http://www.dw.de/a-tale-of-two-substitutes/a-18034715|accessdate=2 November 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=1 November 2014}}</ref> However, the ball went to Lewandowski<ref name=\"A tale of two substitutes\"/> who scored the equaliser.<ref name=\"Bayern restore four-point lead to send Dortmund into bottom three\"/> Robben scored the winning goal from the penalty spot<ref name=\"BVB Richtung Abstiegskampf gedr\u00e4ngt\"/> after Suboti\u0107 fouled Rib\u00e9ry.<ref name=\"A tale of two substitutes\"/> Dortmund goalkeeper [[Roman Weidenfeller]] made several saves during the match.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 2 1 Bor Dortmd\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place<ref name=md10t/> and maintained their four-point lead.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 2 1 Bor Dortmd\"/> Then on 8 November, on matchday 11, Bayern defeated [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] 4\u20130<ref name=\"M\u00fcller erledigt widerspenstige Eintracht\">{{cite news|last1=F\u00fcrst|first1=Dominik|title=M\u00fcller erledigt widerspenstige Eintracht|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fc-bayern-sieg-in-frankfurt-mueller-erledigt-widerspenstige-eintracht-1.2211404|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|accessdate=8 November 2014|language=German|date=8 November 2014}}</ref> with three goals from Thomas M\u00fcller and a goal from Xherdan Shaqiri.<ref name=md11/> M\u00fcller opened the scoring in the 23rd minute.<ref name=\"M\u00fcller erledigt widerspenstige Eintracht\"/> M\u00fcller hit the back of the net three minutes later, however, the referee called offside on the play.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thomas M\u00fcller erledigt Frankfurt im Alleingang|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/eintracht-frankfurt/article134137467/Thomas-Mueller-erledigt-Frankfurt-im-Alleingang.html|accessdate=8 November 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=8 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> Then he got his second goal in the 64th minute and completed his hattrick in the 67th minute.<ref name=\"M\u00fcller erledigt widerspenstige Eintracht\"/> This was M\u00fcller's second hattrick of his career.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chase|first1=Jefferson|title=Bayern roll, Freiburg upset Schalke, and Cologne score four|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-roll-freiburg-upset-schalke-and-cologne-score-four/a-18049268|accessdate=8 November 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=8 November 2014}}</ref> Xherdan Shaqiri then scored in the 86th minute.<ref name=md11/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md11t/> Then on 22 November, on matchday 12, Bayern defeated [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]] 4\u20130 with goals from Mario G\u00f6tze, Robert Lewandowski, Arjen Robben, and [[Sebastian Rode]].<ref name=md12/> G\u00f6tze opened the scoring in the 23rd minute.<ref name=\"Zeit f\u00fcr Bl\u00f6delbilder\">{{cite news|last1=Schmid|first1=Matthias|title=Zeit f\u00fcr Bl\u00f6delbilder|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-gegen-hoffenheim-zeit-fuer-bloedelbilder-1.2233098|accessdate=22 November 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=22 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> Then five minutes before half-time, Lewandowski put Bayern up 2\u20130.<ref name=\"Zeit f\u00fcr Bl\u00f6delbilder\"/> Robben put Bayern up 3\u20130 in the 83rd minute.<ref name=\"Zeit f\u00fcr Bl\u00f6delbilder\"/> Four minutes later, Rode scored to put Bayern up 4\u20130.<ref name=\"Zeit f\u00fcr Bl\u00f6delbilder\"/> [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]] made his first competitive match of the season<ref name=\"Zeit f\u00fcr Bl\u00f6delbilder\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chase|first1=Jefferson|title=Dortmund falter, Schalke squeak by, Bayern cruise|url=http://www.dw.de/dortmund-falter-schalke-squeak-by-bayern-cruise/a-18081005|accessdate=22 November 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=22 November 2014}}</ref> when he came on as a substitute in the 78th minute<ref name=md12/> 1899 Hoffenheim player [[\u00c1d\u00e1m Szalai]] was sent-off in the 90th minute<ref name=md12/> for a foul on [[Dante (footballer)|Dante]].<ref name=\"Bundesligs leaders Bayern Munich cruise to easy win vs. Hoffenheim\">{{cite news|title=Bundesligs leaders Bayern Munich cruise to easy win vs. Hoffenheim|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-bundesliga/story/2157710/bundesligs-leaders-bayern-munich-cruise-to-convincing-victory-over-hoffenheim|accessdate=22 November 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md12t/> Bayern extended their lead to seven points<ref name=\"Bundesligs leaders Bayern Munich cruise to easy win vs. Hoffenheim\"/> after Wolfsburg lost to Schalke 04.<ref>{{cite news|title=Choupo-Motings Doppelpack bringt S04 auf Kurs|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/spieltag/1-bundesliga/2014-15/12/2407327/spielbericht_fc-schalke-04-2_vfl-wolfsburg-24.html|accessdate=22 November 2014|publisher=kicker|date=22 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> On matchday 13, on 29 November,<ref name=md13/> Bayern defeated [[Hertha BSC]] 1\u20130 by a first-half goal from Arjen Robben.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hertha BSC 0 1 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30174008|accessdate=29 November 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=29 November 2014}}</ref> [[Franck Rib\u00e9ry]] tied [[Matthieu Delpierre]] record for most appearances for a [[France|French]] player.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zuvela|first1=Matt|title=Glut of goals in Bundesliga's Saturday matches|url=http://www.dw.de/glut-of-goals-in-bundesligas-saturday-matches/a-18101536|accessdate=29 November 2014|publisher=Deutche Welle|date=29 November 2014}}</ref> With the clean sheet, Bayern tied VfB Stuttgart's record of only three goals conceded in the opening 13 Bundesliga matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich equal record as Arjen Robben goal sinks Hertha Berlin|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/nov/29/hertha-berlin-bayern-munich-bundesliga-match-report|accessdate=30 November 2014|agency=Reuters|publisher=The Guardian|date=29 November 2014}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md13t/>\n\n====December====\nTo start December, Bayern defeated [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] 1\u20130<ref name=\"Erstaunlicher Ecke-Tor-Sieg\">{{cite news|last1=Rosner|first1=Maik|title=Erstaunlicher Ecke-Tor-Sieg|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fc-bayern-gegen-leverkusen-erstaunlicher-ecke-tor-sieg-1.2255518|accessdate=6 December 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=6 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> with [[Franck Rib\u00e9ry]]'s 100th goal for Bayern.<ref name=\"Erstaunlicher Ecke-Tor-Sieg\"/><ref name=md14/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chase|first1=Jefferson|title=Bayern hold on against Leverkusen, Schalke and Wolfsburg win|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-hold-on-against-leverkusen-schalke-and-wolfsburg-win/a-18114074|accessdate=6 December 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=6 December 2014}}</ref> on matchday 14, on 6 December.<ref name=md14/> The goal came in the 51st minute.<ref name=md14/> Bayern had chances to score more goals after taking the lead, by failed to convert any of those chances.<ref name=\"Franck Ribery wins it for Bayern, Wolfsburg and Gladbach victorious\">{{cite news|title=Franck Ribery wins it for Bayern, Wolfsburg and Gladbach victorious|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-bundesliga/story/2183131/franck-ribery-gives-bayern-munich-winwolfsburg-and-monchengladbach-victorious|accessdate=6 December 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=6 December 2014}}</ref> Bayern finished the match in first place,<ref name=md14t/> seven points over second place Wolfsburg.<ref name=\"Franck Ribery wins it for Bayern, Wolfsburg and Gladbach victorious\"/> Then on 13 December, on matchday 15,<ref name=md15/> Bayern defeated [[FC Augsburg]] 4\u20130<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wallrodt|first1=Lars|title=Irdische Kr\u00e4fte k\u00f6nnen diese Bayern nicht stoppen|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-augsburg/article135331497/Irdische-Kraefte-koennen-diese-Bayern-nicht-stoppen.html|accessdate=13 December 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=13 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> with two goals from Arjen Robben and a goal each from Medhi Benatia and Robert Lewandowski.<ref name=md15/> Benatia opened the scoring in the 58th minute.<ref name=\"In 13 Minuten zur Herbstmeisterschaft\">{{cite news|last1=Schmid|first1=Matthias|title=In 13 Minuten zur Herbstmeisterschaft|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/-sieg-des-fc-bayern-in-augsburg-in-minuten-zur-herbstmeisterschaft-1.2266030|accessdate=13 December 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=13 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> Then a minute later, Robben scored his first goal of the match.<ref name=\"In 13 Minuten zur Herbstmeisterschaft\"/> Lewandowski's goal came in the 68th minute before Robben got his second goal of the match three minutes later.<ref name=\"In 13 Minuten zur Herbstmeisterschaft\"/> [[Manuel Neuer]] had touched the ball 64 times during the match and won a free kick \"well outside of the box against [[Tobias Werner]].\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Jonathan|title=Schieber downs Dortmund in the capital, Bayern batter Augsburg|url=http://www.dw.de/schieber-downs-dortmund-in-the-capital-bayern-batter-augsburg/a-18127433|accessdate=13 December 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=13 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md15t/> On 16 December, on matchday 16,<ref name=md16/> Bayern defeated [[SC Freiburg]] 2\u20130<ref name=\"Vergn\u00fcgen mit Doppelkopf\">{{cite news|last1=Jans|first1=Gunnar|title=Vergn\u00fcgen mit Doppelkopf|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-gegen-sc-freiburg-vergnuegen-mit-doppelkopf-1.2270753|accessdate=16 December 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=16 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> with goals from Arjen Robben and Thomas M\u00fcller.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich maintain winning streak against Freiburg|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-bundesliga/story/2201749/bundesliga-bayern-munich-beat-freiburg|accessdate=16 December 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=16 December 2014}}</ref> Robben scored in the 41st minute and M\u00fcller scored in the 48th minute.<ref name=md16/> Robben scored his 100th competitive goal for Bayern.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stuttgart siegt dank Klein-Tor|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/international/Stuttgart-siegt-dank-Klein-Tor/169109314|accessdate=16 December 2014|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=16 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern had a season record 81% possession.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dieser Arjen Robben macht sogar dem Gegner Freude|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article135457458/Dieser-Arjen-Robben-macht-sogar-dem-Gegner-Freude.html|accessdate=16 December 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=16 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md16t/> On matchday 17, on 19 December, Bayern defeated [[1. FSV Mainz 05]] 2\u20131.<ref name=md17/> [[Elkin Soto]] opened the scoring in the 21st minute.<ref name=\"Der FC Bayern bekommt nie genug\">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Der FC Bayern bekommt nie genug|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/spaeter-sieg-in-mainz-der-fc-bayern-bekommt-nie-genug-1.2275621|accessdate=19 December 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=19 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> However, three minutes later, Bastian Schweinsteiger scored the equaliser from a free kick.<ref name=\"Der FC Bayern bekommt nie genug\"/> Then Arjen Robben scored the winning goal with 30 seconds of normal time remaining.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jurejko|first1=Jonathan|title=1. FSV Mainz 05 1 2 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30470610|accessdate=19 December 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=19 December 2014}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place<ref name=md17t/> and the first half of the season undefeated.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich stars fill their boots as Pep Guardiola prepares for nine-day Doha training camp\"/>\n\n====January\u2013February====\nOn matchday 18, on 30 January,<ref name=md18/> Bayern lost their first match of the Bundesliga season<ref name=\"Wolfsburger Zauberstunde\">{{cite news|title=Wolfsburger Zauberstunde|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sieg-gegen-die-bayern-wolfsburger-zauberstunde-1.2329529|accessdate=30 January 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=30 January 2015|language=German}}</ref> and their first league match in 293 days<ref name=\"Die Bayern kassieren eine krachende Niederlage\">{{cite news|title=Die Bayern kassieren eine krachende Niederlage|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article136970562/Die-Bayern-kassieren-eine-krachende-Niederlage.html|accessdate=30 January 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=30 January 2015|language=German}}</ref> after losing 4\u20131 to Wolfsburg.<ref name=\"Wolfsburger Zauberstunde\"/> Bayern had only given up four league goals all season<ref>{{cite news|last1=Humphreys|first1=Philip William|title=Bayern run ends in Wolfsburg thrashing|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-run-ends-in-wolfsburg-thrashing/a-18227104|accessdate=30 January 2015|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=30 January 2015}}</ref> and was the first league match where Bayern gave up four goals since 4 April 2009 when they lost to Wolfsburg 5\u20131.<ref name=\"Die Bayern kassieren eine krachende Niederlage\"/> [[Bas Dost]] and [[Kevin De Bruyne]] each scored two goals for Wolfsburg and [[Juan Bernat]] scored for Bayern.<ref name=md18/> Dost gave Wolfsburg a 1\u20130 league in the fourth minute and added a second in stoppage time in the first half.<ref name=\"Die Bayern kassieren eine krachende Niederlage\"/> Dost became the first player in 102 league matches to score two goals against Bayern.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Begley|first1=Emlyn|title=VfL Wolfsburg 4 1 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30991047|accessdate=30 January 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 January 2015}}</ref> De Bruyne added a third for Wolfsburg in the 53rd minute before Bernat scored two minutes later to give Bayern their only goal of the match.<ref name=\"Die Bayern kassieren eine krachende Niederlage\"/> De Bruyne scored his second goal of the match to put Wolfsburg up 4\u20131.<ref name=\"Die Bayern kassieren eine krachende Niederlage\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md18t/> On matchday 19, on 3 February,<ref name=md19/> Bayern and Schalke 04 finished their match in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref name=\"Vergessen ist die elegante \u00dcberlegenheit\">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Vergessen ist die elegante \u00dcberlegenheit|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-unentschieden-gegen-schalke-vergessen-ist-die-elegante-ueberlegenheit-1.2334446|accessdate=3 February 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=3 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> Arjen Robben opened the scoring in the 67th minute for Bayern and Benedikt H\u00f6wedes equalised in the 72nd minute.<ref name=md19/> [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng]] was sent-off in the 17th minute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Weiser erh\u00e4lt den Vorzug vor G\u00f6tze und M\u00fcller|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article137090998/Weiser-erhaelt-den-Vorzug-vor-Goetze-und-Mueller.html|accessdate=3 February 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=3 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> [[Manuel Neuer]] saved the subsequent penalty shot.<ref name=\"Vergessen ist die elegante \u00dcberlegenheit\"/> Boateng received a three-match ban for the red card<ref name=\"Bayern's Jerome Boateng handed three-match ban for Schalke red card\"/> which was later reduced to two matches.<ref name=\"Sperre reduziert! Boateng fehlt nur noch einmal\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md19t/> On matchday 20, on 7 February,<ref name=md20/> Bayern defeated VfB Stuttgart 2\u20130 with goals from Arjen Robben and David Alaba<ref>{{cite news|title=Zwei Kunstsch\u00fcsse gegen die Harmlosigkeit|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-in-stuttgart-zwei-kunstschuesse-gegen-die-harmlosigkeit-1.2341049|accessdate=7 February 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=7 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> to win their first match of 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=VfB Stuttgart 0 2 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31163316|accessdate=7 February 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=7 February 2015}}</ref> Just before half-time, Robben scored the opening goal of the match.<ref name=\"Aubameyang ends Borussia Dortmund crisis, Bayern labor to victory\">{{cite news|author1=Dunbar, Ross|author2=Harding, Jonathan|title=Aubameyang ends Borussia Dortmund crisis, Bayern labor to victory|url=http://www.dw.de/aubameyang-eases-borussia-dortmund-crisis-bayern-labor-to-victory/a-18242736|accessdate=7 February 2015|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=7 February 2015}}</ref> Then in the 50th minute,<ref name=md20/> Alaba scored from a free kick from about 30 yards out from goal.<ref name=\"Aubameyang ends Borussia Dortmund crisis, Bayern labor to victory\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md20t/> On matchday 21, on 14 February, Bayern defeated Hamburger SV 8\u20130 with two goals each from Thomas M\u00fcller, Mario G\u00f6tze, and Arjen Robben and a goal each from Robert Lewandowski and Franck Rib\u00e9ry.<ref name=md21/> This was Bayern's biggest victory since their 9\u20130 win against [[Kickers Offenbach]] in March 1984.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Garganese|first1=Carlo|title=Bayern Munich\u2019s 8-0 thrashing of Hamburg their biggest win in over 30 years|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/15/germany/2015/02/14/8928422/bayern-munichs-8-0-thrashing-of-hamburg-their-biggest-win-in?ICID=HP_FT_4|accessdate=14 February 2015|publisher=Goal.com|date=14 February 2015}}</ref> In the 21st minute, M\u00fcller opened the scoring from the penalty mark.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sonnabend|first1=Lisa|title=Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-gala-gegen-hsv-diesmal-nur-acht-ohrfeigen-1.2351472|accessdate=14 February 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=14 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> two minutes later, G\u00f6tze put Bayern up 2\u20130.<ref name=\"Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)\">{{cite news|last1=Sonnabend|first1=Lisa|title=Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-gala-gegen-hsv-diesmal-nur-acht-ohrfeigen-1.2351472-2|accessdate=14 February 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=14 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> Robben scored the next two goals.<ref name=md21/> The first goal happened in the 36th minute<ref name=md21/> and the second goal happened in the 47th minute.<ref name=\"Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)\"/> Bayern went up 5\u20130 after M\u00fcller's second goal of the match in the 55th minute.<ref name=\"Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)\"/> Lewandowski made it 6\u20130 a minute later.<ref name=\"Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)\"/> Rib\u00e9ry scored in the 69th minute.<ref name=\"Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)\"/> G\u00f6tze finished the scoring in 88th minute.<ref name=\"Diesmal nur acht Ohrfeigen (page 2)\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md21t/> On matchday 22, on 21 February,<ref name=md22/> Bayern defeated Paderborn 07 6\u20130 with two goals each from Robert Lewandoweski and Arjen Robben and a goal each from Franck Rib\u00e9ry and [[Mitchell Weiser]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Beckenkamp|first1=Jonas|title=Gekommen, um Tore zu schie\u00dfen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-in-paderborn-gekommen-um-tore-zu-schiessen-1.2361548|accessdate=21 February 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=21 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> Lewandowski gave Bayern a 2\u20130 first-half lead when he scored in the 24th and 37th minutes.<ref name=\"Bayern zerlegen Aufsteiger Paderborn\">{{cite news|title=Bayern zerlegen Aufsteiger Paderborn|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/international/Bayern-zerlegen-Aufsteiger-Paderborn/177632721|accessdate=21 February 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|language=German}}</ref> Robben scored from a penalty kick in the 63rd minute.<ref name=\"Bayern zerlegen Aufsteiger Paderborn\"/> [[Florian Hartherz]] was sent-off on the play that led to the penalty shot.<ref>{{cite news|title=SC Paderborn 07 0 6 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31567093|accessdate=21 February 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 February 2015}}</ref> Rib\u00e9ry scored in the 72nd minute<ref name=\"Bayern zerlegen Aufsteiger Paderborn\"/> and Weiser scored his first Bundesliga goal<ref name=\"Bayern Munich awakening from winter-break hibernation\">{{cite news|last1=Lovell|first1=Mark|title=Bayern Munich awakening from winter-break hibernation|url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/bayern-munich/132/blog/post/2313384/bayern-munich-awakening-from-winter-break-hibernation|accessdate=23 February 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=23 February 2015}}</ref> in the 78th minute before Robben got his second of the match in the 86th minute.<ref name=\"Bayern zerlegen Aufsteiger Paderborn\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md22t/> On matchday 23, on 27 February, Bayern defeated 1. FC K\u00f6ln 4\u20131.<ref name=md23/> Bastian Schweinsteiger, Franck Rib\u00e9ry, Arjen Robben, and Robert Lewandowski scored for Bayern and [[Anthony Ujah]] scored for K\u00f6ln.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern fertigen auch K\u00f6ln ab|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/international/Bayern-fertigen-auch-Koeln-ab/178521913|accessdate=27 February 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=27 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> Bayern took a 2\u20130 lead inside the first 10 minutes when Schweinsteiger scored off of a corner kick in the third minute and Rib\u00e9ry goal in the 10th minute.<ref name=\"Die Bayern straucheln nur kurz\">{{cite news|title=Die Bayern straucheln nur kurz|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sieg-gegen-koeln-die-bayern-straucheln-nur-kurz-1.2371854|accessdate=27 February 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=27 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> Ujah pulled a goal back when he scored during stoppage time in the first half.<ref name=\"Die Bayern straucheln nur kurz\"/> Robben and Lewandowski both scored in the second half to give Bayern the 4\u20131 lead.<ref name=\"Die Bayern straucheln nur kurz\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md23t/>\n\n====March====\nOn matchday 24, on 7 March, Bayern defeated Hannover 96 3\u20131.<ref name=md24/> Bayern got two goals from Thomas M\u00fcller and a goal from Xabi Alonso and [[Hiroshi Kiyotake]] scored for Hannover.<ref>{{cite news|title=Schwerf\u00e4llige Bayern m\u00fchen sich zum 19. Saisonsieg|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/hannover-96/article138165064/Schwerfaellige-Bayern-muehen-sich-zum-19-Saisonsieg.html|accessdate=7 March 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=7 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> Kiyotake Gave Hannover the lead in the 25th minute.<ref name=\"3:1 - Bayern drehen Partie in Hannover\">{{cite news|title=3:1 - Bayern drehen Partie in Hannover|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/international/31-Bayern-drehen-Partie-in-Hannover/179478364|accessdate=7 March 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=7 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> Then Xabi Alonso scored the equaliser from a free kick in the 28th minute.<ref name=\"3:1 - Bayern drehen Partie in Hannover\"/> Then M\u00fcller scored from a penalty kick in the 61st minute. He got his second goal of the match 11 minutes later to put Bayern up 3\u20131.<ref name=\"3:1 - Bayern drehen Partie in Hannover\"/> [[Dante (footballer)|Dante]] came off in the 32nd minute and was replaced by Robert Lewandowski.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Jonathan|title=M\u00fcller drags Bayern Munich over the line|url=http://www.dw.de/m%C3%BCller-drags-bayern-munich-over-the-line/a-18301918|accessdate=7 March 2015|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=7 March 2015}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place<ref name=md24t/> and took an 11-point lead after VfL Wolfsburg lost to FC Augsburg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich stretch lead as M\u00fcller sees off Hannover and Wolfsburg slip|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/07/hannover-bayern-munich-bundesliga-match-report|accessdate=7 March 2015|agency=Reuters|publisher=The Guardian|date=7 March 2015}}</ref> On matchday 25, on 14 March, Bayern defeated Werder Bremen 4\u20130 with two goals from Robert Lewandowski and a goal each from Thomas M\u00fcller and David Alaba.<ref name=md25/> M\u00fcller scored in the 24th minute and Alaba scored in stoppage time in the first half to give Bayern a 2\u20130 first half lead.<ref name=\"Bayern zerlegt Bremen beim Lahm-Comeback\">{{cite news|title=Bayern zerlegt Bremen beim Lahm-Comeback|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/article138413541/Bayern-zerlegt-Bremen-beim-Lahm-Comeback.html|accessdate=14 March 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=14 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> Lewandowski scored in the 76th minute and stoppage time in the second half to put Bayern up 4\u20130.<ref name=\"Bayern zerlegt Bremen beim Lahm-Comeback\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md25t/> On matchday 26, on 22 March, Bayern lost to Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach 2\u20130<ref name=md26/> with two goals, in 30th and 77th minutes, by [[Raffael Caetano de Ara\u00fajo|Raffael]].<ref>{{cite news|title=M\u00f6nchengladbach entzauberte die Bayern|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/Moenchengladbach-entzauberte-die-Bayern/181587104|accessdate=23 March 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=22 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> The loss meant that Bayern's six-match winning streak came to an end<ref>{{cite news|title=Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach end Bayern Munich\u2019s six-match winning run|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/22/bayern-munich-borussia-monchengladbach-match-report|accessdate=24 March 2015|publisher=The Guardian|date=22 March 2015}}</ref> and they lost at [[Allianz Arena]] for the first time since losing to [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] in April 2014.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 0 2 Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Mun 0 2 Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31991990|accessdate=23 March 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=22 March 2015}}</ref> Arjen Robben came off in the 24th minute after he tore an abdominal muscle.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 0 2 Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md26t/>\n\n====April====\nOn matchday 27, on 4 April, Bayern defeated Borussia Dortmund 1\u20130 with a 36th-minute goal from Robert Lewandowski.<ref name=md27/> Lewandowski scored from a header after [[Roman Weidenfeller]] \"parried\" Thomas M\u00fcller's shot.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bor Dortmd 0 1 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32121014|accessdate=4 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=4 April 2015}}</ref> Bayern and Dortmund came into the match with a 31-point difference in the league table.<ref name=\"Lewandowski setzt die Pointe\">{{cite news|last1=Rosner|first1=Maik|title=Lewandowski setzt die Pointe|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-gegen-dortmund-lewandowski-setzt-die-pointe-1.2422765|accessdate=4 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=4 April 2015|location=Dortmund|language=German}}</ref> Four players for Bayern were out with various injuries.<ref name=\"Lewandowski setzt die Pointe\"/> Bastian Schweinsteiger was injured during the match.<ref name=\"Bastian Schweinsteiger is latest injury blow for Bayern Munich as Germany captain suffers ankle injury\">{{cite news|title=Bastian Schweinsteiger is latest injury blow for Bayern Munich as Germany captain suffers ankle injury|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3027368/Bastian-Schweinsteiger-latest-injury-blow-Bayern-Munich-Germany-captain-suffers-ankle-injury.html|accessdate=6 April 2015|agency=Reuters|publisher=Daily Mail|date=6 April 2015}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=November 2019}} However, [[Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara|Thiago]] made his first appearance since his injury and Philipp Lahm made his first start since his injury.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rosner|first1=Maik|title=Tr\u00e4nen nach 371 Tagen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/thiago-rueckkehr-beim-fc-bayern-traenen-nach-tagen-1.2422788|accessdate=5 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=5 April 2015|location=Dortmund|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md27t/> On matchday 28, on 11 April,<ref name=md28/> Bayern defeated Eintracht Frankfurt 3\u20130 with two goals from Robert Lewandowski and a goal from Thomas M\u00fcller.<ref name=\"Rumpfkader zaubert\">{{cite news|last1=Rosner|first1=Maik|title=Rumpfkader zaubert|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-gegen-frankfurt-rumpfkader-zaubert-1.2430975|accessdate=11 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=11 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> Lewandowski gave Bayern a 1\u20130 lead in the 15th minute and put Bayern up 2\u20130 in the 66th minute.<ref name=md28/> M\u00fcller scored Bayern's third goal in the 82nd minute.<ref name=md28/> Seven players were out due to injury.<ref name=\"Rumpfkader zaubert\"/> Bayern finished the match in first place.<ref name=md28t/> On matchday 29, on 18 April,<ref name=md29/> Bayern defeated 1899 Hoffenheim 2\u20130 with a 38th-minute goal from [[Sebastian Rode]] and a second half stoppage time own goal from [[Andreas Beck (footballer)|Andreas Beck]].\n<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern besiegen Hoffenheim mit 2:0|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/international/Bayern-besiegen-Hoffenheim-mit-20/184974535|accessdate=18 April 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=18 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md29t/> On matchday 30, on 25 April,<ref name=md30/> Bayern defeated Hertha BSC 1\u20130 with a goal from Bastian Schweinsteiger.<ref name=\"Schweinsteiger macht Bayern zum 99,9-Prozent-Meister\">{{cite news|last1=Rosner|first1=Maik|title=Schweinsteiger macht Bayern zum 99,9-Prozent-Meister|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sieg-gegen-hertha-schweinsteiger-macht-bayern-zum-prozent-meister-1.2452640|accessdate=25 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=25 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> Schweinsteiger scored in the 80th minute after Mitchell Weiser crossed the ball to him.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Mun 1 0 Hertha BSC|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32450223|accessdate=25 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=25 April 2015}}</ref> [[Javi Mart\u00ednez]] was in the squad for the first time in 255 days.<ref name=md30/> Pep Guardiola made five changes to the starting 11 from the Champions League match against [[FC Porto|Porto]] in mid-week.<ref name=md30/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=md30t/> The following day, Bayern won their 25th German championship (24th Bundesliga championship), and 3rd consecutive championship, after Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach defeated VfL Wolfsburg 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich: Pep Guardiola's side win club's 25th German title|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32475479|accessdate=27 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=26 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n====May====\nOn matchday 31, on 2 May, Bayern lost to Bayer Leverkusen 2\u20130 with goals from [[Hakan \u00c7alhano\u011flu]] and [[Julian Brandt]].<ref name=\"Wie ein m\u00e4\u00dfig motivierter Au\u00dfenseiter\">{{cite news|last1=Selldorf|first1=Philipp|title=Wie ein m\u00e4\u00dfig motivierter Au\u00dfenseiter|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-niederlage-in-leverkusen-wie-ein-maessig-motivierter-aussenseiter-1.2461938|accessdate=2 May 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=2 May 2015|language=German}}</ref> \u00c7alhano\u011flu scored in the 55th minute from a free kick and Brandt scored in the 81st minute.<ref name=md31/> Pep Guardiola made seven changes from their mid-week German Cup match<ref name=md31/> including [[Rico Strieder]],<ref name=md31/> who made his professional debut,<ref name=\"Zwei Bayern-Youngster mit ordentlichen Profi-Deb\u00fcts\">{{cite news|title=Zwei Bayern-Youngster mit ordentlichen Profi-Deb\u00fcts|url=http://www.tz.de/sport/fc-bayern/rico-strieder-lukas-goertler-zwei-fc-bayern-youngster-feiern-ordentliche-debuets-meta-4963920.html|accessdate=2 May 2015|publisher=TZ|date=2 May 2015|language=German}}</ref> and [[Javi Mart\u00ednez]], who made his season debut in the Bundesliga.<ref name=\"Wie ein m\u00e4\u00dfig motivierter Au\u00dfenseiter\"/> [[Lukas G\u00f6rtler]], who came on in the 72nd minute, also made his professional debut.<ref name=\"Zwei Bayern-Youngster mit ordentlichen Profi-Deb\u00fcts\"/> On matchday 32, on 9 May, Bayern lost to FC Augsburg 1\u20130 with a 71st-minute goal from [[Ra\u00fal Bobadilla]].<ref name=md32/> [[Pepe Reina]] received a red card in the 13th minute.<ref name=md13/> [[Paul Verhaegh]] hit the post in the subsequent penalty shot<ref name=\"Historische Niederlage f\u00fcr Bayern-Coach Guardiola\">{{cite news|title=Historische Niederlage f\u00fcr Bayern-Coach Guardiola|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article140715033/Historische-Niederlage-fuer-Bayern-Coach-Guardiola.html|accessdate=9 May 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=9 May 2015|language=German}}</ref> and Reina eventually received a two-match suspension for the red card.<ref name=\"Pepe Reina banned for two matches after Bayern Munich red card\">{{cite news|last1=Uersfeld|first1=Stephan|title=Pepe Reina banned for two matches after Bayern Munich red card|url=http://www.espnfc.com/bayern-munich/story/2445374/pepe-reina-banned-for-two-matches-after-bayern-munich-red|accessdate=23 May 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=12 May 2015}}</ref> Dante also picked up a suspension after receiving his fifth yellow card of the season.<ref name=\"Guardiola hat Wunschliste im Kopf\">{{cite news|title=Guardiola hat Wunschliste im Kopf|url=http://www.tz.de/sport/fc-bayern/gluecklicher-guardiola-hat-wunschliste-im-kopf-zr-5011654.html|accessdate=23 May 2015|publisher=tz|date=16 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> This was the first time since October 1991 that Bayern lost four in a row (in all competitions and including shoot-out losses).<ref name=\"Historische Niederlage f\u00fcr Bayern-Coach Guardiola\"/> On 16 May, on matchday 33, Bayern lost 2\u20131 to SC Freiburg.<ref name=md33/> Bastian Schweinsteiger, gave Bayern the lead in the 13th minute.<ref name=\"Sport-Club Freiburg 2 1 Bayern Mun\">{{cite news|title=Sport-Club Freiburg 2 1 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32760732|accessdate=21 May 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=16 May 2015}}</ref> [[Admir Mehmedi]] equalized in the 33rd minute<ref name=\"Sport-Club Freiburg 2 1 Bayern Mun\"/> and [[Nils Petersen]] scored the winner in the 89th minute.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cataldo|first1=Filippo|title=Petersen l\u00e4sst Freiburg erbeben|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sieg-gegen-fc-bayern-petersen-laesst-freiburg-erbeben-1.2481452|accessdate=21 May 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=16 May 2015|language=German}}</ref> This was Bayern's fifth loss in six matches in all competitions.<ref name=\"Sport-Club Freiburg 2 1 Bayern Mun\"/> This was also the first time Freiburg beat Bayern since 9 March 1996.<ref name=md33/> On matchday 34, on 23 May, Bayern defeated Mainz 05 2\u20130 with a goal from the penalty mark from Robert Lewandowski in the 25th minute and a 48th-minute goal from Bastian Schweinsteiger.<ref name=md34/> Schweinsteiger played in his 500th match for Bayern.<ref>{{cite news|title=Meister Bayern freut sich auf Partymarathon|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article141400170/Meister-Bayern-freut-sich-auf-Partymarathon.html|accessdate=23 May 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=23 May 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n\n===Bundesliga table===\n{{2014\u201315 Bundesliga table|showteam=FCB}}\n\n===Bundesliga results summary===\n{{Fb rs |hw=14 |hd=1 |hl=2 |hgf=46 |hga=7 |aw=11 |ad=3 |al=3 |agf=34 |aga=11 }}\n{{Fb rs footer |u=23 May 2015 |s=[http://ww