:30\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[BayArena|A]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | {{nowrap|0\u20130 ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])}}<br>{{Nowrap|(5\u20133 [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|p]])}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 30,210\n| [[Dante (footballer)|Dante]] {{yel|71}}<br>[[Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara|Thiago]] {{yel|90+3}}<br>[[Thomas M\u00fcller|M\u00fcller]] {{yel|116}}\n| [[Lars Bender|Bender]] {{yel|50}}<br>[[\u00d6mer Toprak|Toprak]] {{yel|104}}<br>[[Kyriakos Papadopoulos|Papadopoulos]] {{yel|116}}<br>[[Tin Jedvaj|Jedvaj]] {{yel|117}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref name=qf>{{cite news|title=Drmic versagen die Nerven - FCB steht im Semifinale!|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2014-15/4/2835070/spielbericht_bayer-leverkusen-9_bayern-muenchen-14.html|accessdate=8 April 2015|date=8 April 2015|language=German}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|title=DFB-Pokal, 2014/15, Viertelfinale|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2014-15/4/2835070/spielverlauf_bayer-leverkusen-9_bayern-muenchen-14.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=8 April 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| colspan=\"2\" | '''[[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|Penalties]]'''\n|- style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| style=\"text-align: right;\" | [[Thomas M\u00fcller|M\u00fcller]] {{pengoal}}&nbsp;<br>[[Robert Lewandowski|Lewandowski]] {{pengoal}}&nbsp;<br>[[Xabi Alonso|Alonso]] {{pengoal}}&nbsp;<br>[[Mario G\u00f6tze|G\u00f6tze]] {{pengoal}}&nbsp;<br>[[Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara|Thiago]] {{pengoal}}&nbsp;\n| style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: top;\" | &nbsp;{{penmiss}} [[Josip Drmi\u0107|Drmi\u0107]]<br>&nbsp;{{pengoal}} [[Lars Bender|Bender]]<br>&nbsp;{{pengoal}} [[Gonzalo Castro|Castro]]<br>&nbsp;{{pengoal}} [[Hakan \u00c7alhano\u011flu|\u00c7alhano\u011flu]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"8\"| [[2014\u201315 DFB-Pokal#FC Bayern Munich v Borussia Dortmund|Semifinals]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 28 April<br>20:30\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Allianz Arena|H]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | {{Nowrap|1\u20131 ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])}}<br>{{Nowrap|(0\u20132 [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|p]])}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 75,000\n| [[Robert Lewandowski|Lewandowski]] {{goal|29}}<br>[[Rafinha (footballer, born 1985)|Rafinha]] {{yel|64}}<br>[[Xabi Alonso|Alonso]] {{yel|72}}<br>[[Medhi Benatia|Benatia]] {{yel|113}}\n| [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang|Aubameyang]] {{goal|75}}<br>[[Kevin Kampl|Kampl]] {{sent off|2|90|108}}<br>[[Sokratis Papastathopoulos|Papastathopoulos]] {{yel|101}}<br>[[Mitchell Langerak|Langerak]] {{yel|120}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref name=sf>{{cite news|title=BVB steht dank Bayern-Ausrutschern im Finale|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2014-15/5/2837086/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_borussia-dortmund-17.html|accessdate=28 April 2015|newspaper=kicker|date=28 April 2015|language=German}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|title=DFB-Pokal, 2014/15, Halbfinale|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/spielrunde/dfb-pokal/2014-15/5/2837086/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_borussia-dortmund-17.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=28 April 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| colspan=\"2\" | '''[[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|Penalties]]'''\n|- style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| style=\"text-align: right;\" | [[Philipp Lahm|Lahm]] {{penmiss}}&nbsp;<br>[[Xabi Alonso|Alonso]] {{penmiss}}&nbsp;<br>[[Mario G\u00f6tze|G\u00f6tze]] {{penmiss}}&nbsp;<br>[[Manuel Neuer|Neuer]] {{penmiss}}&nbsp;\n| style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: top;\" | &nbsp;{{pengoal}} [[\u0130lkay G\u00fcndo\u011fan|G\u00fcndo\u011fan]]<br>&nbsp;{{pengoal}} [[Sebastian Kehl|Kehl]]<br>&nbsp;{{penmiss}} [[Mats Hummels|Hummels]]\n|}\n\n==DFL-Supercup==\n{{main|2014 DFL-Supercup}}\n\n===DFL-Supercup review===\nBayern faced [[Borussia Dortmund]] in the [[2014 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]] on 13 August.<ref name=\"supercup\"/> Borussia Dortmund won the match 2\u20130 with goals from [[Henrikh Mkhitaryan]] and [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hartmann|first1=Ulrich|title=Dortmund hebt den Zeigefinger|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sieg-im-supercup-dortmund-hebt-den-zeigefinger-1.2088890|accessdate=13 August 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=13 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> [[Javi Mart\u00ednez]] left the match injured<ref name=\"Dortmund dominate Bayern to claim Supercup\">{{cite news|last1=Hallam|first1=Mark|title=Dortmund dominate Bayern to claim Supercup|url=http://www.dw.de/dortmund-dominate-bayern-to-claim-supercup/a-17852924|accessdate=14 August 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=13 August 2014}}</ref> after [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|tearing his ACL]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Javi Martinez: Bayern Munich midfielder ruled out for rest of year|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28793723|accessdate=14 August 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=14 August 2014}}</ref> This was the third consecutive year where Bayern has faced Borussia Dortmund in the competition.<ref name=\"Supercup: FCB und BVB treffen sich sp\u00e4ter\"/> Bayern won the [[DFL-Supercup|super cup]] in [[2012 DFL-Supercup|2012]] 2\u20131 and Borussia Dortmund won in [[2013 DFL-Supercup|2013]] 4\u20132.<ref name=\"Supercup: FCB und BVB treffen sich sp\u00e4ter\"/> The match was originally scheduled for four days earlier.<ref name=\"Supercup: FCB und BVB treffen sich sp\u00e4ter\">{{cite news|title=Supercup: FCB und BVB treffen sich sp\u00e4ter|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/605230/artikel_supercup_fcb-und-bvb-treffen-sich-spaeter.html|accessdate=3 June 2014|publisher=kicker|date=28 May 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern was without [[Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara|Thiago]],<ref name=\"Bayern Munich\u2019s Thiago Alc\u00e2ntara suffers setback with knee injury\"/> [[Franck Rib\u00e9ry]],<ref name=\"Rafinha erleidet Au\u00dfenbandriss - Pause f\u00fcr Ribery\">{{cite news|title=Rafinha erleidet Au\u00dfenbandriss - Pause f\u00fcr Ribery|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/609445/artikel_rafinha-erleidet-aussenbandriss---pause-fuer-ribery.html|accessdate=12 August 2014|publisher=kicker|date=10 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> and [[Rafinha (footballer, born 1985)|Rafinha]].<ref name=\"Rafinha erleidet Au\u00dfenbandriss - Pause f\u00fcr Ribery\"/> [[Sebastian Rode]], [[Gianluca Gaudino]], [[Juan Bernat]], and [[Robert Lewandowski]] made their debuts for Bayern.<ref name=\"Dortmund dominate Bayern to claim Supercup\"/>\n\n===DFL-Supercup result===\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Date<br>Kick-off<ref group=n name=time />\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|H/A|Home or away venue}}\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Opponent\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|Res.|Results}}<br>{{Abbr|F\u2013A|Goals for\u2013goals against}}\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|Att.|Match attendance}}\n!colspan=\"2\"| Goalscorers and disciplined players\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! style=\"width:180px\"| [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]\n! style=\"width:180px\"| Opponent\n|- style=\"background:#fcc\"\n| 13 August<br>18:00\n| [[Westfalenstadion|A]]\n| [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| 0\u20132\n| 80,667\n| [[Pierre-Emile H\u00f8jbjerg|H\u00f8jbjerg]] {{yel|45}}<br>[[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng|Boateng]] {{yel|73}}<br>[[Philipp Lahm|Lahm]] {{yel|85}}\n| [[Henrikh Mkhitaryan|Mkhitaryan]] {{goal|23}}<br>[[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang|Aubameyang]] {{goal|62}}\n| <ref name=\"supercup\">{{cite news|title=Aubameyang k\u00f6pft BVB zum Supercup-Sieg|url=http://www.kicker.de/d-supercup-fb-1/2014/1/2396815/spielbericht_borussia-dortmund-17_bayern-muenchen-14.html|accessdate=13 August 2014|newspaper=kicker|date=13 August 2014|language=German}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==UEFA Champions League==\n{{main|2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League}}\n\n===Group stage===\n{{main|2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group E}}\n\n====Group stage review====\n[[File:CSKA-Bavaria (9).jpg|thumb|142px|Thomas M\u00fcller playing against CSKA Moscow]]\n\nBayern were drawn into Group E with [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]], and [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Madrid to meet former champs Liverpool in Champions League group stage|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2014/08/28/madrid-faces-former-champions-liverpool-in-group-stage|accessdate=28 August 2014|agency=Reuters|publisher=[[Toronto Sun]]|date=28 August 2014|location=Monaco}}</ref> Bayern started their Champions League campaign<ref name=\"Erl\u00f6st durch Boatengs Wuchtgeschoss\">{{cite news|title=Erl\u00f6st durch Boatengs Wuchtgeschoss|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-erfolg-gegen-mancity-erloest-durch-boatengs-wuchtgeschoss-1.2134319|accessdate=17 September 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=17 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> on 17 September<ref name=uclmd1t/> with a 1\u20130 win against Manchester City.<ref name=uclmd1/> [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng]] scored for Bayern<ref name=\"Erl\u00f6st durch Boatengs Wuchtgeschoss\"/> after a slight deflection from [[Mario G\u00f6tze]].<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 1 0 Man City\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Mun 1 0 Man City|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29225435|accessdate=17 September 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=17 September 2014}}</ref> [[Medhi Benatia]], made his official debut for Bayern, where he played for 85 minutes, completing 93% of his passes. During the match, [[Joe Hart]] \"denied\" Bayern with a \"series of saves.\"<ref name=\"Champions League: Bayern Munich\u2019s last-minute goal beats Manchester City\">{{cite news|last1=Dunbar|first1=Graham|title=Champions League: Bayern Munich\u2019s last-minute goal beats Manchester City|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/soccer/2014/09/17/champions_league_bayern_munichs_lastminute_goal_beats_manchester_city.html#|accessdate=23 September 2014|agency=The Associated Press|publisher=Toronto Star|date=17 September 2014}}</ref> The goal was Bayern's 800th goal in all European competitions.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 1 0 Man City\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in second place.<ref name=uclmd1t/> On matchday two of the group stage, on 30 September, Bayern defeated CSKA Moscow 1\u20130<ref name=uclmd2/> with a goal from a penalty shot from Thomas M\u00fcller<ref name=\"Guardiola hadert mit seiner wackligen Abwehr\">{{cite news|title=Guardiola hadert mit seiner wackligen Abwehr|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article132793487/Guardiola-hadert-mit-seiner-wackligen-Abwehr.html|accessdate=30 September 2014|publisher=Die Welt|language=German}}</ref> after Mario G\u00f6tze was fouled by [[M\u00e1rio Fernandes (footballer)|M\u00e1rio Fernandes]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Thomas Muller penalty enough for Bayern to beat CSKA Moscow|url=http://www.espnfc.us/uefa-champions-league/story/2063506/thomas-muller-penalty-enough-for-bayern-to-beat-cska-moscow|accessdate=30 September 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=30 September 2014}}</ref> The match had no supporters in the stadium<ref name=\"Minimalistisch vor blauen Sitzschalen\">{{cite news|last1=Eberts|first1=Carsten|title=Minimalistisch vor blauen Sitzschalen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-bei-zska-moskau-minimalistisch-vor-blauen-sitzschalen-1.2154530|accessdate=30 September 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=30 September 2014|language=German}}</ref> because of racist behaviour of CSKA Moscow supporters.<ref>{{cite news|title=CSKA 0 1 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29362540|accessdate=1 October 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=30 September 2014}}</ref> However, several Bayern supporters who made the trip to [[Moscow]] for the match saw the match from a skyscraper.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern-Fans tricksen UEFA aus|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/Bayern-Fans-tricksen-UEFA-aus/159772437|accessdate=1 October 2014|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=1 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> This was the 100th win for Bayern in Champions League history.<ref name=\"Guardiola hadert mit seiner wackligen Abwehr\"/> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=uclmd2t/> Then Bayern defeated [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] 7\u20131<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pugmire|first1=Jerome|title=Cristiano Ronaldo propels Real Madrid over Liverpool|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/soccer/2014/10/22/cristiano_ronaldo_propels_real_madrid_over_liverpool.html|accessdate=27 October 2014|agency=Associated Press|publisher=Toronto Star|date=22 October 2014|location=Paris}}</ref> on matchday three on 21 October.<ref name=uclmd3/> Bayern got two goals from [[Arjen Robben]] and a goal each from Mario G\u00f6tze, [[Robert Lewandowski]], Thomas M\u00fcller, [[Franck Rib\u00e9ry]], and [[Xherdan Shaqiri]] and [[Gervinho]] scored for Roma.<ref>{{cite news|title=FC Bayern l\u00e4sst AS Rom erstarren|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/champions-league-fc-bayern-laesst-as-rom-erstarren-1.2185186|accessdate=21 October 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=21 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> Gervinho's goal ended Bayern's streak of 813 minutes without conceding a goal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Roma 1 7 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29362752|accessdate=21 October 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=21 October 2014}}</ref> The win was Bayern's biggest away win in Champions League history.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern schon vor dem Segen des Papstes \u00fcberirdisch|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/champions-league/article133520476/Bayern-schon-vor-dem-Segen-des-Papstes-ueberirdisch.html|accessdate=21 October 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=21 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place.<ref name=uclmd3t/> In the return match against Roma, on matchday four, on 5 November, Bayern won 2\u20130<ref name=uclmd4/> with goals from Franck Rib\u00e9ry and Mario G\u00f6tze.<ref name=uclmd4/> Rib\u00e9ry opened the scoring in the 38th minute.<ref name=\"FC Bayern spaziert im Rekordtempo ins Achtelfinale\">{{cite news|title=FC Bayern spaziert im Rekordtempo ins Achtelfinale|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article134038133/FC-Bayern-spaziert-im-Rekordtempo-ins-Achtelfinale.html|accessdate=6 November 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=5 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> Rib\u00e9ry and David Alaba created a 2-on-1 situation on the left flank.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich secure Group E, Schalke lose\">{{cite news|last1=Dunbar|first1=Ross|title=Bayern Munich secure Group E, Schalke lose|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-munich-secure-group-e-schalke-lose/a-18044055|accessdate=6 November 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=5 November 2014}}</ref> Alaba passed the ball back to Rib\u00e9ry who scored from the edge of the box.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich secure Group E, Schalke lose\"/> G\u00f6tze scored the other goal in the 64th minute<ref name=\"FC Bayern spaziert im Rekordtempo ins Achtelfinale\"/> after Lewandowski pulled away from his marker and crossed the ball to him.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich secure Group E, Schalke lose\"/> [[Manuel Neuer]] had to pull off a \"double save.\"<ref name=\"Bayern Munich cruise to knockout stages with easy win over Roma\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich cruise to knockout stages with easy win over Roma|url=http://www.espnfc.com/uefa-champions-league/match/405713/bayern-munich-as-roma/report|accessdate=5 November 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=5 November 2014}}</ref> Alaba picked up a knee ligament injury in the match.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich's David Alaba suffers knee ligament injury|url=http://www.espnfc.us/bayern-munich/story/2131330/bayern-munichs-david-alaba-suffers-knee-ligament-injury|accessdate=5 November 2014|publisher=ESPN FC|date=5 November 2014}}</ref> Bayern finished the matchday in first place,<ref name=uclmd4t/> and with the win, Bayern clinched top spot in Group E.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich cruise to knockout stages with easy win over Roma\"/> This was Bayern's quickest path to the knockout round to date.<ref name=\"FC Bayern spaziert im Rekordtempo ins Achtelfinale\"/> Bayern also became the first German club to win the Group with two matches to spare.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich secure Group E, Schalke lose\"/> Then on matchday five, on 25 November,<ref name=uclmd5/> Manchester City defeated Bayern 3\u20132.<ref name=\"Aussetzer beim Betriebsausflug\">{{cite news|title=Aussetzer beim Betriebsausflug|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/-niederlage-in-manchester-aussetzer-beim-betriebsausflug-1.2237852|accessdate=25 November 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=25 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> Xabi Alonso and Robert Lewandowski scored for Bayern and [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero]] scored three goals from Manchester City.<ref name=uclmd5/> Ag\u00fcero scored the opening goal from the penalty spot.<ref name=uclmd5/> Medhi Benatia was sent-off on the play that led up to the penalty shot.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Jonathan|title=Aguero takes Bayern gifts to seal win, Schalke self-destruct at home|url=http://www.dw.de/aguero-takes-bayern-gifts-to-seal-win-schalke-self-destruct-at-home/a-18088766|accessdate=25 November 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=25 November 2014}}</ref> The following day, he received a one-match ban for the red card.<ref name=\"Nach Rot: Medhi Benatia nur f\u00fcr ein Spiel gesperrt\"/> Alonso equalised when he scored from a free kick in the 40th minute.<ref name=uclmd5/> Five minutes later, Lewandowski scored to give Bayern a 2\u20131 lead.<ref name=uclmd5/> [[Stevan Joveti\u0107]] picked out an Alonso pass and then passed it to Ag\u00fcero,<ref>{{cite news|title=Guardiola baut nach roter Karte um|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/-niederlage-in-manchester-aussetzer-beim-betriebsausflug-1.2237852-2|accessdate=25 November 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=25 November 2014|language=German}}</ref> who scored in the 85th minute.<ref name=uclmd5/> Then Ag\u00fcero scored in stoppage time to give Manchester City a 3\u20132 lead.<ref name=uclmd5/> On 10 December, Bayern finished the group stage with a 3\u20130 win against CSKA Moscow<ref name=uclmd6/> with goals from Thomas M\u00fcller, [[Sebastian Rode]] and Mario G\u00f6tze.<ref name=\"Ein Abend f\u00fcr Experimente\">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Ein Abend f\u00fcr Experimente|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-sieg-gegen-zska-moskau-ein-abend-fuer-experimente-1.2262199|accessdate=10 December 2014|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=10 December 2014|language=German}}</ref> M\u00fcller opened the scoring in the 18th minute from the penalty spot.<ref name=\"Ein Abend f\u00fcr Experimente\"/> This was his record-breaking 24th goal in UEFA Champions League for Bayern.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich knock CSKA Moscow out with easy home win\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich knock CSKA Moscow out with easy home win|url=http://www.espnfc.us/uefa-champions-league/match/405676/bayern-munich-cska-moscow/report|accessdate=10 December 2014|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=10 December 2014}}</ref> Rode and G\u00f6tze rounded out the scoring in the 84th and 90th minutes.<ref name=\"Ein Abend f\u00fcr Experimente\"/> [[Gianluca Gaudino]] played in his first UEFA Champions League match.<ref name=\"Ein Abend f\u00fcr Experimente\"/>\n\n====Group E table====\n{{2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League Group E|showteam=BAY}}\n\n====Group stage results summary====\n{{Fb_rs |hw=3 |hd=0 |hl=0 |hgf=6 |hga=0 |aw=2 |ad=0 |al=1 |agf=10 |aga=4}}\n{{Fb_rs_footer|u=15 December 2014|s=[[#Group E fixtures and results|Champions League Group Stage ma