}\n| \u2014\n| 1\n| 12\n| <ref name=uclmd4>{{cite news|title=Ribery findet die L\u00fccke im Roma-Abwehrnetz|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2014-15/4/2798660/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_as-rom.html|accessdate=5 November 2014|newspaper=kicker|date=5 November 2014|language=German}}</ref><br><ref name=uclmd4t>{{cite web|title=Champions League - Spieltag / Tabelle|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2014-15/4/3310/spieltag.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=5 November 2014|language=German}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|title=Bayern M\u00fcnchen - AS Rom live (05.11.2014, Vorrunde Gruppe E)|url=http://liveticker.sueddeutsche.de/fussball/champions-league/bayern-muenchen/as-rom/2014-11-05.html|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|accessdate=5 November 2014|language=German|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106011756/http://liveticker.sueddeutsche.de/fussball/champions-league/bayern-muenchen/as-rom/2014-11-05.html|archive-date=6 November 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#fcc\"\n| [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage#Manchester City v Bayern Munich|5]]\n| 25 November<br>20:45\n| [[City of Manchester Stadium|A]]\n| [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n| 2\u20133\n| 47,726\n| [[Medhi Benatia|Benatia]] {{sent off|0|21}}<br>[[Xabi Alonso|Alonso]] {{goal|40}}<br>[[Robert Lewandowski|Lewandowski]] {{goal|45}}<br>[[Manuel Neuer|Neuer]] {{yel|78}}\n| [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero|Ag\u00fcero]] {{goal|21|pen.|85||90+1}}, {{yel|90+2}}<br>[[Ga\u00ebl Clichy|Clichy]] {{yel|60}}<br> [[Pablo Zabaleta|Zabaleta]] {{yel|90}}\n| 1\n| 12\n| <ref name=uclmd5>{{cite news|title=Alonso und Boateng servieren f\u00fcr Aguero|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2014-15/5/2798645/spielbericht_manchester-city-1343_bayern-muenchen-14.html|accessdate=25 November 2014|newspaper=kicker|date=25 November 2014|language=German}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|title=Champions League - Spieltag / Tabelle|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2014-15/5/3310/spieltag.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=25 November 2014|language=German}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|title=Manchester City - Bayern M\u00fcnchen live (25.11.2014, Vorrunde Gruppe E)|url=http://liveticker.sueddeutsche.de/fussball/champions-league/manchester-city/bayern-muenchen/2014-11-25.html|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|accessdate=25 November 2014|language=German|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141125091030/http://liveticker.sueddeutsche.de//fussball/champions-league/manchester-city/bayern-muenchen/2014-11-25.html|archive-date=25 November 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage#Bayern Munich v CSKA Moscow|6]]\n| 10 December<br>20:45\n| [[Allianz Arena|H]]\n| [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]\n| 3\u20130\n| 68,000\n| [[Thomas M\u00fcller|M\u00fcller]] {{goal|18|pen.}}<br>[[Dante (footballer)|Dante]] {{yel|68}}<br>[[Sebastian Rode|Rode]] {{goal|84}}<br>[[Mario G\u00f6tze|G\u00f6tze]] {{goal|90}}\n| [[Bibras Natkho|Natkho]] {{yel|27}}<br>[[Alan Dzagoev|Dzagoev]] {{yel|70}}<br>[[Sergei Ignashevich|Ignashevich]] {{yel|90+2}}\n| 1\n| 15\n| <ref name=uclmd6>{{cite news|title=M\u00fcller, Rode und G\u00f6tze erledigen ZSKA|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2014-15/6/2798655/spielbericht_bayern-muenchen-14_zska-moskau-1572.html|accessdate=10 December 2014|newspaper=kicker|date=10 December 2014|language=German}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Knockout phase===\n{{main|2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League knockout phase}}\n\n====Knockout phase review====\nOn 5 November, after beating A.S. Roma 2\u20130, Bayern Munich won the group and qualified for the knockout phase.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich secure Group E, Schalke lose\"/> In the round of 16 draw, on 15 December, Bayern were drawn against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Champions League: PSG-Chelsea, Man City-Barca, Arsenal-Monaco|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30477407|accessdate=15 December 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=15 December 2014}}</ref> In the first leg, on 17 February, the match finished in a 0\u20130 draw.<ref name=\"Nullnummer: FC Bayern tut sich bei Donezk schwer\">{{cite news|title=Nullnummer: FC Bayern tut sich bei Donezk schwer|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/chleague/spielrunde/champions-league/2014-15/7/2826626/spielbericht_schachtjor-donezk_bayern-muenchen-14.html|accessdate=17 February 2015|newspaper=kicker|date=17 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> The match was played in [[Lviv]].<ref name=\"Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich\">{{cite news|last1=Reddy|first1=Luke|title=Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/31508728|accessdate=17 February 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 February 2015}}</ref> Xabi Alonso, who played in his 100th Champions League match,<ref name=\"Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich\"/> was sent-off<ref name=\"Nullnummer: FC Bayern tut sich bei Donezk schwer\"/> after receiving a second yellow card.<ref name=\"Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich\"/> [[Douglas Costa]] received a yellow card after he elbowed Franck Rib\u00e9ry.<ref name=\"Shakhtar holds Bayern after Xabi Alonso is sent off\">{{cite news|title=Shakhtar holds Bayern after Xabi Alonso is sent off|url=http://www.espnfc.us/uefa-champions-league/match/410548/shakhtar-donetsk-bayern-munich/report|accessdate=17 February 2015|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=17 February 2015}}</ref> There was 35 fouls and eight yellow cards in the match.<ref name=\"Shakhtar holds Bayern after Xabi Alonso is sent off\"/> The second leg took place on 11 March.<ref name=\"7:0! FC Bayern dank Torgala im Achtelfinale\"/> Bayern defeated Shakhtar Donetsk 7\u20130 with two goals from Thomas M\u00fcller and a goal each from J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng, Franck Rib\u00e9ry, [[Holger Badstuber]], Robert Lewandowski and Mario G\u00f6tze.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\">{{cite news|title=FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/champions-league-fc-bayern-duest-ins-viertelfinale-1.2389807|accessdate=11 March 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=11 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> Bayern won on aggregate by the same scoreline.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 7 0 Shakt Donsk\">{{cite news|last1=Cryer|first1=Andy|title=Bayern Mun 7 0 Shakt Donsk|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31816155|accessdate=11 March 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=11 March 2015}}</ref> M\u00fcller gave Bayern the lead in the fourth minute from a penalty shot.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> [[Oleksandr Kucher]] was sent-off on the play leading top the penalty shot.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> This was the \"quickest\" red card to be shown in Champions League history.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 7 0 Shakt Donsk\"/><ref name=\"Bayern Munich hit seven past 10-man Shakhtar Donetsk to reach last eight\">{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich hit seven past 10-man Shakhtar Donetsk to reach last eight|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/11/bayern-munich-shakhtar-donetsk-champions-league-match-report|accessdate=12 March 2015|agency=Associated Press|publisher=The Guardian|date=11 March 2015}}</ref> Arjen Robben left the match injured in the 19th minute.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich hit seven past 10-man Shakhtar Donetsk to reach last eight\"/> Boateng made it 2\u20130 in the 34th minute.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> In the 49th minute, Rib\u00e9ry scored to put Bayern up 3\u20130.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> Bayern went up 4\u20130 when M\u00fcller got his second of the match in the 52nd minute.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> Rib\u00e9ry left the match in the 60th minute due to an ankle injury.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich hit seven past 10-man Shakhtar Donetsk to reach last eight\"/> Badstuber scored in the 63rd minute to put Bayern up by 5.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> This was his first goal since December 2009.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zitouni|first1=Mounir|title=Badstuber auf der \u00dcberholspur|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/622959/artikel_badstuber-auf-der-ueberholspur.html|accessdate=26 March 2015|publisher=kicker|date=13 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> Lewandowski scored in the 75th minute to make it 6\u20130.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> It was 7\u20130 when G\u00f6tze scored in the 88th minute.<ref name=\"FC Bayern d\u00fcst ins Viertelfinale\"/> The scoreline tied for the biggest win in the club's Champions League history.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 7 0 Shakt Donsk\"/>\n\nIn the quarterfinal draw, Bayern were drawn against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Champions League: Atletico Madrid v Real Madrid in last eight|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31984955|accessdate=20 March 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=20 March 2015}}</ref> This is Bayern's fourth straight quarterfinal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich cruises to Champions League quarter-finals|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/soccer/2015/03/11/bayern-munich-cruises-to-champions-league-quarter-finals.html|accessdate=20 March 2015|agency=The Associated Press|publisher=Toronto Star|date=11 March 2015}}</ref> The first leg took place on 15 April.<ref name=uclqffl/> Porto won the first leg 3\u20131.<ref name=\"Der Wunschgegner bereitet Albtr\u00e4ume\">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Der Wunschgegner bereitet Albtr\u00e4ume|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayern-niederlage-beim-fc-porto-der-wunschgegner-bereitet-albtraeume-1.2437683|accessdate=15 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=15 April 2015|location=Porto|language=German}}</ref> Thiago scored for Bayern and Porto got two goals from [[Ricardo Quaresma]] and a goal from [[Jackson Mart\u00ednez]].<ref name=uclqffl/> Quaresma scored two goals in the first 10 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Porto shock Bayern Munich 3-1 in quarterfinal first leg; Quaresma brace|url=http://www.espnfc.us/uefa-champions-league/match/418413/fc-porto-bayern-munich/report|accessdate=15 April 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=15 April 2015}}</ref> For the first goal, Quaresma scored from a penalty shot in the third minute after Manuel Neuer tripped Mart\u00ednez inside the penalty area.<ref name=\"FC Porto 3 1 Bayern Mun\">{{cite news|last1=Hafez|first1=Shamoon|title=FC Porto 3 1 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32295979|accessdate=15 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 April 2015}}</ref> Neuer received a yellow card on the play.<ref name=\"Der Wunschgegner bereitet Albtr\u00e4ume\"/> For his second goal in the 10th minute, Quaresma \"nicking the ball from Dante\" to set-up the goal.<ref name=\"FC Porto 3 1 Bayern Mun\"/> Then in the 28th minute, Thiago put Bayern on the scoreboard.<ref name=\"FC Porto 3 1 Bayern Mun\"/> Mart\u00ednez scored in the 65th minute to make it 3\u20131.<ref name=\"FC Porto 3 1 Bayern Mun\"/> The loss finished Bayern's 11-match undefeated streak in Portugal.<ref name=\"FC Porto 3 1 Bayern Mun\"/> The following day, [[Hans-Wilhelm M\u00fcller-Wohlfahrt]],<ref name=\"Ende eines Machtkampfs mit Guardiola\">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Ende eines Machtkampfs mit Guardiola|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/ruecktritt-von-mueller-wohlfahrt-ende-eines-machtkampfs-mit-guardiola-1.2439445|accessdate=16 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=16 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> along with three other members of the medical team,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Uersfeld|first1=Stephan|title=Pep Guardiola: Bayern doctor quitting changes nothing; Philipp Lahm out|url=http://www.espnfc.us/bayern-munich/story/2404015/pep-guardiola-bayern-doctor-quitting-changes-nothingphilipp-lahm-out|accessdate=17 April 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=17 April 2015}}</ref> resigned after the medical team was blamed for the loss.<ref name=\"Ende eines Machtkampfs mit Guardiola\"/> The second leg took place on 21 April.<ref name=uclqfsl/> Bayern defeated Porto 6\u20131 and 7\u20134 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern use huge first half to demolish Porto, reach semifinals|url=http://www.espnfc.us/uefa-champions-league/match/418410/bayern-munich-fc-porto/report|accessdate=21 April 2015|agency=PA Sport|publisher=ESPN FC|date=21 April 2015}}</ref> Bayern got two goals from Robert Lewandowski and a goal each from Thiago, J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng, Thomas M\u00fcller, and Xabi Alonso.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Catuogno|first1=Claudio|title=Bayern pfeift auf den Ballast|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/viertelfinale-der-champions-league-bayern-pfeift-auf-den-ballast-1.2446563|accessdate=21 April 2015|publisher=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=21 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> Jackson scored for Porto.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\">{{cite news|last1=Begley|first1=Emlyn|title=Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32380841|accessdate=21 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 April 2015}}</ref> Bayern took a 2\u20130 lead within the first 22 minutes with goals from Thiago and Boateng.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\"/> Lewendowski put Bayern up by three in the 27th minute.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\"/> Bayern were up 4\u20130 after M\u00fcller scored in the 36th minute.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\"/> With the goal, he became the highest scoring German in the competition's history.<ref name=\"Bayern routs Porto reach Champions semis\">{{cite news|last=Starcevic|first=Nesha|title=Bayern routs Porto reach Champions semis|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/soccer/2015/04/21/bayern-routs-porto-reach-champions-semis.html|accessdate=22 April 2015|agency=The Associated Press|publisher=Toronto Star|date=21 April 2015}}</ref> Lewandowski got his second goal of the match when he scored in the 40th minute.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\"/> Jackson scored for Porto in the 73rd minute and Alonso scored in the 88th minute from a free kick.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\"/> The free kick was given after [[Iv\u00e1n Marcano]] fouled Thiago, in which he was sent-off for a second yellow card for Porto.<ref name=\"Bayern routs Porto reach Champions semis\"/> The win sent Bayern to their fourth consecutive semifinal.<ref name=\"Bayern Mun 6 1 FC Porto\"/> This was [[Pep Guardiola]]'s 100th match as head coach.<ref name=uclqfsl/>\n\nIn the semifinal draw, Bayern were drawn against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Champions League: Barcelona v Bayern, Juventus v Real Madrid|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32443182|accessdate=24 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 April 2015}}</ref> The match took place on 6 May.<ref name=uclsffl/> Barcelona won the first leg 3\u20130 with two goals from [[Lionel Messi]] and a goal from [[Neymar]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Barca schie\u00dft Bayern 3:0 ab|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/europacup/Champions-League-Barca-schiesst-Bayern-30-ab/187259172|accessdate=6 May 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=6 May 2015|language=German}}</ref> The score remained 0\u20130 until the 77th minute when Messi scored.<ref name=\"Barcelona 3 0 Bayern Mun\">{{cite news|last1=Henson|first1=Mike|title=Barcelona 3 0 Bayern Mun|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32582198|accessdate=6 May 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 May 2015}}</ref> Messi added his second of the match three minutes later.<ref name=\"Barcelona 3 0 Bayern Mun\"/> Neymar added Barcelona's third goal in stoppage time.<ref name=uclsffl/> Bayern failed to get a shot on target for the first time since October 2009 when they lost to [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Girondins de Bordeaux]].<ref name=\"Barcelona 3 0 Bayern Mun\"/> The second leg took place on 12 May.<ref name=uclsfsl/> Bayern won the match 3\u20132, however, Bayern lost 5\u20133 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Starcevic|first1=Nesha|title=Barcelona advances to Champions League final|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/soccer/2015/05/12/barcelona-advances-to-champions-league-final.html|accessdate=12 May 2015|publisher=Toronto Star|date=12 May 2015}}</ref> Medhi Benatia, Robert Lewandowski, and Thomas M\u00fcller scored for Bayern and Neymar scored twice for Barcelona.<ref name=\"3:2 - Bayern siegt, Barcelona jubelt\">{{cite news|title=3:2 - Bayern siegt, Barcelona jubelt|url=http://sport.oe24.at/fussball/international/Champions-League-32-Bayern-siegt-Barcelona-jubelt/188121155|accessdate=12 May 2015|publisher=\u00d6sterreich|date=12 May 2015|language=German}}</ref> Benatia gave Bayern a 1\u20130 lead in the seventh minute.<ref name=\"3:2 - Bayern siegt, Barcelona jubelt\"/> Then Neymar scored in the 15th and 29th minutes.<ref name=\"3:2 - Bayern siegt, Barcelona jubelt\"/> Then Lewandowski and M\u00fcller scored in the second half.<ref name=\"3:2 - Bayern siegt, Barcelona jubelt\"/> The win ended Bayern's four match losing streak.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jurejko|first1=Jonathan|title=Bayern Mun 3 2 Barcelona|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32683310|accessdate=12 May 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=12 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Knockout phase results====\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" Style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Leg\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Date<br>Kick-off<ref group=n name=time />\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|H/A|Home or away venue}}\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Opponent\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|Res.|Results}}<br>{{Abbr|F\u2013A|Goals for\u2013goals against}}\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|Agg. score|Aggregate score}}<br>{{Abbr|F\u2013A|Goals for\u2013goals against}}\n!rowspan=\"2\"| {{Abbr|Att.|Attendance}}