<ref name=\"Bayern's Jerome Boateng handed three-match ban for Schalke red card\"/> However, after appeal,<ref name=\"Boateng drei Spiele gesperrt - Bayern legt Berufung ein\">{{cite news|title=Boateng drei Spiele gesperrt - Bayern legt Berufung ein|trans-title=|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fussball/Boateng-drei-Spiele-gesperrt-Bayern-legt-Berufung-ein-id32907087.html|accessdate=6 February 2015|publisher=Augsburger Allgemeine|date=5 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> the ban was reduced to two matches.<ref name=\"Sperre reduziert! Boateng fehlt nur noch einmal\"/> [[Xabi Alonso]] was sent off for two bookable offences<ref name=\"Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich\"/> and missed the return leg on 11 March.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich awakening from winter-break hibernation\"/> Alonso also picked up his fifth yellow card against [[Hannover 96]] on 7 March<ref name=md24/> and was suspended<ref name=md24/> for the match against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on 14 March. During the match against Werder Bremen, Benatia picked up a fifth yellow card and was suspended for the match on 22 March against [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]].<ref name=md26/> Pepe Reina received a two-match suspension after his red card against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref name=\"Pepe Reina banned for two matches after Bayern Munich red card\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! Player\n! No. of <br> matches served\n! Reason\n! Competition\n! Date served\n! Opponent(s)\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Red card vs. Hamburger SV\n| [[Bundesliga]] ([[2013\u201314 FC Bayern Munich season|2013\u201314 season]])\n| 10 May\n| [[VfB Stuttgart]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref name=\"Boateng verpasst Saisonauftakt\">{{cite news|title=Boateng verpasst Saisonauftakt|trans-title=|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fussball-bundesliga-boateng-verpasst-saisonauftakt-1.1951127|accessdate=5 May 2014|newspaper=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=5 May 2014|language=German}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Bundesliga]] (2014\u201315 season)\n| 22 August\n| [[VfL Wolfsburg]]\n|-\n| [[Medhi Benatia]]\n| 1\n| Suspension from [[2013\u201314 Coppa Italia]]\n| [[2014\u201315 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]]\n| 29 October\n| [[Hamburger SV]]\n| <ref name=\"Altlasten aus Italien: Benatia im Pokal gesperrt\">{{cite news|last1=Zitouni|first1=Mounir|title=Altlasten aus Italien: Benatia im Pokal gesperrt|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/dfbpokal/startseite/614271/artikel_altlasten-aus-italien_benatia-im-pokal-gesperrt.html|accessdate=27 November 2014|publisher=kicker|date=28 October 2014|language=German}}</ref>\n|-\n| Medhi Benatia\n| 1\n| Red card vs. [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n| [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]\n| 10 December\n| [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]\n| <ref name=\"Nach Rot: Medhi Benatia nur f\u00fcr ein Spiel gesperrt\">{{cite news|title=Nach Rot: Medhi Benatia nur f\u00fcr ein Spiel gesperrt|url=http://www.abendzeitung-muenchen.de/inhalt.fc-bayern-star-nach-rot-mehdi-benatia-nur-fuer-ein-spiel-gesperrt.bfd4abc4-c9c7-4083-839f-793ce48ff9b1.html|accessdate=27 November 2014|publisher=Abendzeitung|date=27 November 2014|language=German}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Red card vs. [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Bundesliga\n| 7 February\n| [[VfB Stuttgart]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| <ref name=\"Sperre reduziert! Boateng fehlt nur noch einmal\">{{cite news|author1=Linkesch, Frank|author2=Schr\u00f6ter, Carsten|title=Sperre reduziert! Boateng fehlt nur noch einmal|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/620790/artikel_sperre-reduziert-boateng-fehlt-nur-noch-einmal.html|accessdate=9 February 2015|publisher=kicker|date=9 February 2015|language=German}}</ref>\n|-\n| 14 February\n| [[Hamburger SV]]\n|-\n| [[Xabi Alonso]]\n| 1\n| Red Card vs. [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|