ainst [[Hamburger SV|Hamburg]]\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n*[[Manuel Neuer]] won the [[Footballer of the Year in Germany|German footballer of the year]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Manuel Neuer named German Footballer of the Year|url=http://www.dw.de/manuel-neuer-named-german-footballer-of-the-year/a-17844354|accessdate=15 August 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=10 August 2014}}</ref>\n*Manuel Neuer, [[Arjen Robben]], [[Philipp Lahm]], and [[Thomas M\u00fcller]] were among the top 10 players nominated for [[UEFA Best Player in Europe Award]].<ref name=\"Manuel Neuer, Arjen Robben & Cristiano Ronaldo on Uefa award list\">{{cite news|title=Manuel Neuer, Arjen Robben & Cristiano Ronaldo on Uefa award list|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28793705|accessdate=15 August 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=14 August 2014}}</ref> Manuel Neuer and Arjen Robben joined [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] from [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] on the shortlisted for the award.<ref name=\"Manuel Neuer, Arjen Robben & Cristiano Ronaldo on Uefa award list\"/> Ronaldo won the award.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ronaldo wins another European award for his museum|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2014/08/28/ronaldo-wins-another-european-award-for-his-museum|accessdate=28 August 2014|agency=Reuters|publisher=Toronto Sun|date=28 August 2014|location=Monaco}}</ref>\n*[[Mario G\u00f6tze]], Philipp Lahm, Thomas M\u00fcller, Manuel Neuer, Arjen Robben and Bastian Schweinsteiger were nominated to the [[2014 FIFA Ballon d'Or]] shortlist and [[Pep Guardiola]] was named to the shortlist for the FIFA World Coach of the Year for Men's Football.<ref>{{cite news|title=Six Germans nominated in FIFA World Footballer of the Year list|url=http://www.dw.de/six-germans-nominated-in-fifa-world-footballer-of-the-year-list/a-18024867|accessdate=3 December 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=28 October 2014}}</ref> On 1 December 2014, Neuer was nominated as a final three candidate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Neuer, Ronaldo and Messi make Ballon d'Or final three|url=http://www.dw.de/neuer-ronaldo-and-messi-make-ballon-dor-final-three/a-18104534|accessdate=3 December 2014|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=1 December 2014}}</ref> On 12 January 2015, he finished third in the voting.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cristiano Ronaldo wins Ballon d\u2019Or over Lionel Messi & Manuel Neuer|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/30783885|accessdate=12 January 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=12 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[David Alaba]] was named the [[Austrian footballer of the year]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich's Alaba named Austrian Footballer of the Year|url=http://www.dw.de/bayern-munichs-alaba-named-austrian-footballer-of-the-year/a-18140518|accessdate=16 February 2015|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n*Manuel Neuer, David Alaba, Philipp Lahm, and Arjen Robben were voted in to the UEFA Team of the Year.<ref name=\"Bayern dominate UEFA Team of the Year poll\"/>\n*Manuel Neuer, Philipp Lahm, Arjen Robben, and [[2013-14 FC Bayern Munich season|last-years']] player [[Toni Kroos]] were voted in to the FIFA/FIFPro World XI 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/ballon-dor/world11/ |title=FIFA/FIFPro World XI 2014 |accessdate=14 February 2015 |publisher=[[FIFA]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150214224245/http://www.fifa.com/ballon-dor/world11/ |archivedate=14 February 2015 }}</ref>\n*[[Robert Lewandowski]] was named Polish player of the year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Striker Robert Lewandowski named Poland's Player of the Year again|url=http://www.espnfc.com/bayern-munich/story/2288104/bayern-munich-striker-robert-lewandowski-named-polands-player-of-the-year|accessdate=14 February 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=8 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reserve team==\n{{main|Bayern Munich II}}\n\n===Summary===\n[[Bayern Munich II]] play in the fourth-tier [[Regionalliga Bayern]] for a third consecutive season. They were coached by [[Erik ten Hag]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Warmbrunn|first=Benedikt|title=Unterrichter in kniffligen Fragen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/bayerns-nachwuchscoach-erik-ten-hag-unterrichter-in-kniffligen-fragen-1.1690603|accessdate=24 August 2014|newspaper=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=6 June 2013|language=German}}</ref>\n\n===Squad===\nSource:<ref>{{cite web|title=Regionalliga Bayern - Bayern M\u00fcnchen II|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/rlby/regionalliga-bayern-2012/2014-15/bayern-muenchen-ii-88/kader.html|website=kicker.de|publisher=kicker|accessdate=8 December 2014|language=German}}</ref>\n<!-- keep the redlinks because this will become a historical article and notability will change -->\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|pos=GK|nat=Austria|name=[[Ivan Lu\u010di\u0107 (footballer, born 1995)|Ivan Lucic]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|pos=DF|nat=Germany|name=[[Herbert Paul (footballer)|Herbert Paul]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|pos=DF|nat=Germany|name=[[Philipp Steinhart]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|pos=DF|nat=Germany|name=[[Stefan Buck]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|pos=DF|nat=Germany|name=Edwin Schwarz}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|pos=MF|nat=Germany|name=[[Rico Strieder]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|pos=FW|nat=Germany|name=[[Tobias Schweinsteiger]]|other=[[Captain (association football)|captain]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|pos=DF|nat=Austria|name=[[Ylli Sallahi]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|pos=FW|nat=Germany|name=[[Gerrit Wegkamp]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|pos=FW|nat=Germany|name=Bastian Fischer}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|pos=FW|nat=Germany|name=Patrick Weihrauch}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|pos=GK|nat=Germany|name=[[Andreas R\u00f6ssl]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|pos=DF|nat=Germany|name=[[Giuseppe Leo]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|pos=MF|nat=France|name=[[Steeven Rib\u00e9ry]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=15|pos=DF|nat=Germany|name=[[Matthias Strohmaier]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=16|pos=MF|nat=Greece|name=[[Angelos Oikonomou]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|pos=MF|nat=Germany|name=[[Lukas G\u00f6rtler]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=18|pos=MF|nat=Germany|name=[[Kodjovi Koussou]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|pos=MF|nat=Germany|na