|url=http://www.espnfc.com/bayern-munich/story/2283306/bayern-munich-defender-jerome-boateng-three-match-ban-schalke-red-card|accessdate=5 February 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=5 February 2015}}</ref> He was originally given a three-match ban.<ref name=\"Bayern's Jerome Boateng handed three-match ban for Schalke red card\"/> However, after appeal,<ref name=\"Boateng drei Spiele gesperrt - Bayern legt Berufung ein\">{{cite news|title=Boateng drei Spiele gesperrt - Bayern legt Berufung ein|trans-title=|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fussball/Boateng-drei-Spiele-gesperrt-Bayern-legt-Berufung-ein-id32907087.html|accessdate=6 February 2015|publisher=Augsburger Allgemeine|date=5 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> the ban was reduced to two matches.<ref name=\"Sperre reduziert! Boateng fehlt nur noch einmal\"/> [[Xabi Alonso]] was sent off for two bookable offences<ref name=\"Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich\"/> and missed the return leg on 11 March.<ref name=\"Bayern Munich awakening from winter-break hibernation\"/> Alonso also picked up his fifth yellow card against [[Hannover 96]] on 7 March<ref name=md24/> and was suspended<ref name=md24/> for the match against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on 14 March. During the match against Werder Bremen, Benatia picked up a fifth yellow card and was suspended for the match on 22 March against [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]].<ref name=md26/> Pepe Reina received a two-match suspension after his red card against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref name=\"Pepe Reina banned for two matches after Bayern Munich red card\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! Player\n! No. of <br> matches served\n! Reason\n! Competition\n! Date served\n! Opponent(s)\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Boateng]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Red card vs. Hamburger SV\n| [[Bundesliga]] ([[2013\u201314 FC Bayern Munich season|2013\u201314 season]])\n| 10 May\n| [[VfB Stuttgart]